    <section id=3D"abstract" class=3D"introductory"><h2>Abstract</h2>
      This specification extends <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D=
"HTMLMediaElement" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.htm=
l#htmlmediaelement"><code>HTMLMediaElement</code></a> [<cite><a class=3D"bi=
bref" data-link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/=
#bib-html" title=3D"HTML Standard">HTML</a></cite>] to allow JavaScript to =
generate
      media streams for playback. Allowing JavaScript to generate streams f=
acilitates a variety of
      use cases like adaptive streaming and time shifting live streams.
    </section>
    <section id=3D"sotd" class=3D"introductory"><h2>Status of This Document=
</h2><p><em>This section describes the status of this
      document at the time of its publication. A list of current <abbr titl=
e=3D"World Wide Web Consortium">W3C</abbr>
      publications and the latest revision of this technical report can be =
found
      in the
      <a href=3D"https://www.w3.org/TR/"><abbr title=3D"World Wide Web Cons=
ortium">W3C</abbr> standards and drafts index</a>.</em></p>
      <p>
        On top of editorial updates, substantive changes since publication =
as a <abbr title=3D"World Wide Web Consortium">W3C</abbr> Recommendation
        in <a href=3D"https://www.w3.org/TR/2016/REC-media-source-20161117/=
">November 2016</a> are:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>the addition of a <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"changeTy=
pe()" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-sourcebuffer-changety=
pe" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-sourcebuffer-changetype-1"><cod=
e>changeType</code></a><code>()</code> method to switch among codecs or
        bytestreams
        </li>
        <li>the possibility to create and use <a data-link-type=3D"idl" dat=
a-lt=3D"MediaSource" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-medias=
ource" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource-1"><code>MediaSo=
urce</code></a> objects off the main thread in
        dedicated workers
        </li>
        <li>the removal of the <a data-link-type=3D"method" data-lt=3D"crea=
teObjectURL()" href=3D"https://www.w3.org/TR/FileAPI/#dfn-createObjectURL">=
<code>createObjectURL</code></a><code>()</code> extension to the <a data-li=
nk-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"URL" href=3D"https://url.spec.whatwg.org/#=
url"><code>URL</code></a> object following
        its integration in the File API [<cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-lin=
k-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#bib-fileapi" =
title=3D"File API">FILEAPI</a></cite>]
        </li>
        <li>the addition of <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"ManagedMed=
iaSource" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-managedmediasourc=
e" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-managedmediasource-1"><code>Mana=
gedMediaSource</code></a>, <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"ManagedSour=
ceBuffer" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-managedsourcebuff=
er" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-managedsourcebuffer-1"><code>Ma=
nagedSourceBuffer</code></a>, and
        <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"BufferedChangeEvent" href=3D"h=
ttps://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-bufferedchangeevent" class=3D"intern=
alDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-bufferedchangeevent-1"><code>BufferedChangeEvent</=
code></a> interfaces supporting power-efficient streaming and active buffer=
ed
        media cleanup by the user agent
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        For a full list of changes made since the previous version, see the=
 <a href=3D"https://github.com/w3c/media-source/commits/main">commits</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        The working group maintains <a href=3D"https://github.com/w3c/media=
-source/issues">a list of
        all bug reports that the editors have not yet tried to address</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        Implementors should be aware that this specification is not stable.=
 <strong>Implementors
        who are not taking part in the discussions are likely to find the s=
pecification changing
        out from under them in incompatible ways.</strong> Vendors interest=
ed in implementing this
        specification before it eventually reaches the Candidate Recommenda=
tion stage should track
        the <a href=3D"https://github.com/w3c/media-source">GitHub reposito=
ry</a> and take part in
        the discussions.
      </p>
