    <section id=3D"introduction" class=3D"informative"><div class=3D"header=
-wrapper"><h2 id=3D"x1-introduction"><bdi class=3D"secno">1. </bdi>
        Introduction
      </h2><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-sourc=
e/#introduction" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 1."></a></div><p><em>T=
his section is non-normative.</em></p>
     =20
      <p>
        This specification allows JavaScript to dynamically construct media=
 streams for
        &lt;audio&gt; and &lt;video&gt;. It defines a MediaSource object th=
at can serve as a source
        of media data for an HTMLMediaElement. MediaSource objects have one=
 or more
        <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"SourceBuffer" href=3D"https://=
w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-sourcebuffer" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"r=
ef-for-dom-sourcebuffer-1"><code>SourceBuffer</code></a> objects. Applicati=
ons append data segments to the <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"Source=
Buffer" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-sourcebuffer" class=
=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-sourcebuffer-2"><code>SourceBuffer</code=
></a>
        objects, and can adapt the quality of appended data based on system=
 performance and other
        factors. Data from the <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"SourceB=
uffer" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-sourcebuffer" class=
=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-sourcebuffer-3"><code>SourceBuffer</code=
></a> objects is managed as track buffers for audio,
        video and text data that is decoded and played. Byte stream specifi=
cations used with these
        extensions are available in the byte stream format registry [<cite>=
<a class=3D"bibref" data-link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io=
/media-source/#bib-mse-registry" title=3D"Media Source Extensions=E2=84=A2 =
Byte Stream Format Registry">MSE-REGISTRY</a></cite>].
      </p>
      <figure id=3D"fig-media-source-pipeline-model-diagram">
        <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/pipeline_model_descri=
ption.html#pipelinedesc"><picture><img src=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-s=
ource/pipeline_model.svg" alt=3D"Media Source Pipeline Model Diagram" width=
=3D"800" height=3D"629"></picture></a>
        <figcaption><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/me=
dia-source/#fig-media-source-pipeline-model-diagram">Figure <bdi class=3D"f=
igno">1</bdi></a> <span class=3D"fig-title">
          Media Source Pipeline Model Diagram
        </span></figcaption>
      </figure>
      <section id=3D"goals"><div class=3D"header-wrapper"><h3 id=3D"x1-1-go=
als"><bdi class=3D"secno">1.1 </bdi>
          Goals
        </h3><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-sou=
rce/#goals" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 1.1"></a></div>
       =20
        <p>
          This specification was designed with the following goals in mind:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Allow JavaScript to construct media streams independent of ho=
w the media is fetched.
          </li>
          <li>Define a splicing and buffering model that facilitates use ca=
ses like adaptive
          streaming, ad-insertion, time-shifting, and video editing.
          </li>
          <li>Minimize the need for media parsing in JavaScript.
          </li>
          <li>Leverage the browser cache as much as possible.
          </li>
          <li>Provide requirements for byte stream format specifications.
          </li>
          <li>Not require support for any particular media format or codec.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          This specification defines:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Normative behavior for user agents to enable interoperability=
 between user agents and
          web applications when processing media data.
          </li>
          <li>Normative requirements to enable other specifications to defi=
ne media formats to be
          used within this specification.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>
    </section>
    <section id=3D"definitions"><div class=3D"header-wrapper"><h2 id=3D"x2-=
definitions"><bdi class=3D"secno">2. </bdi>
        Definitions
      </h2><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-sourc=
e/#definitions" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 2."></a></div>
     =20
      <dl>
        <dt>
          <dfn id=3D"dfn-active-track-buffers" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=
=3D"dialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">Active Track Buffers</dfn>
        </dt>
        <dd>
          <p>
            The <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.g=
ithub.io/media-source/#track-buffer" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-tr=
ack-buffer-1">track buffers</a> that provide <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstr=
act-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-coded-frame" class=
=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-coded-frame-1">coded frames</a> for the =
<a data-link-type=3D"attribute" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multip=
age/media.html#dom-audiotrack-enabled"><code>enabled</code></a>
            <a data-link-type=3D"attribute" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatw=
g.org/multipage/media.html#dom-media-audiotracks"><code>audioTracks</code><=
/a>, the <a data-link-type=3D"attribute" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.o=
rg/multipage/media.html#dom-videotrack-selected"><code>selected</code></a>
            <a data-link-type=3D"attribute" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatw=
g.org/multipage/media.html#dom-media-videotracks"><code>videoTracks</code><=
/a>, and the <code><a href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.=
html#dom-texttrack-showing">"showing"</a></code> or
            <code><a href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.h=
tml#dom-texttrack-hidden">"hidden"</a></code> <a data-link-type=3D"attribut=
e" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#dom-media-text=
tracks"><code>textTracks</code></a>. All these tracks
            are associated with <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"Source=
Buffer" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-sourcebuffer" class=
=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-sourcebuffer-4"><code>SourceBuffer</code=
></a> objects in the <a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=3D"https://w3c.github.i=
o/media-source/#dom-mediasource-activesourcebuffers" class=3D"internalDFN" =
id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource-activesourcebuffers-1"><code>activeSourceBuff=
ers</code></a>
            list.
          </p>
        </dd>
        <dt>
          <dfn id=3D"dfn-append-window" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dia=
log" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">Append Window</dfn>
        </dt>
        <dd>
          <p>
            A <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.git=
hub.io/media-source/#presentation-timestamp" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"re=
f-for-presentation-timestamp-1">presentation timestamp</a> range used to fi=
lter out <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.i=
o/media-source/#dfn-coded-frame" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-co=
ded-frame-2">coded frames</a> while appending.
            The append window represents a single continuous time range wit=
h a single start time
            and end time. Coded frames with <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstra=
ct-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#presentation-timestamp" =
class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-presentation-timestamp-2">presentation =
timestamp</a> within this range are
            allowed to be appended to the <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=
=3D"SourceBuffer" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-sourcebuf=
fer" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-sourcebuffer-5"><code>SourceBu=
ffer</code></a> while coded frames outside this range
            are filtered out. The append window start and end times are con=
trolled by the
            <a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-s=
ource/#dom-sourcebuffer-appendwindowstart" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-=
for-dom-sourcebuffer-appendwindowstart-1"><code>appendWindowStart</code></a=
> and <a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/=
#dom-sourcebuffer-appendwindowend" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-=
sourcebuffer-appendwindowend-1"><code>appendWindowEnd</code></a> attributes
            respectively.
          </p>
        </dd>
        <dt>
          <dfn class=3D"export" data-export=3D"" data-plurals=3D"coded fram=
es" id=3D"dfn-coded-frame" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog" data-dfn=
-type=3D"dfn">Coded Frame</dfn>
        </dt>
        <dd>
          <p>
            A unit of media data that has a <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstra=
ct-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#presentation-timestamp" =
class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-presentation-timestamp-3">presentation =
timestamp</a>, a <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.=
github.io/media-source/#dfn-decode-timestamp" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"r=
ef-for-dfn-decode-timestamp-1">decode timestamp</a>, and
            a <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.git=
hub.io/media-source/#dfn-coded-frame-duration" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"=
ref-for-dfn-coded-frame-duration-1">coded frame duration</a>.
          </p>
        </dd>
        <dt>
          <dfn id=3D"dfn-coded-frame-duration" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=
=3D"dialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">Coded Frame Duration</dfn>
        </dt>
        <dd>
          <p>
            The duration of a <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D=
"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-coded-frame" class=3D"internalDFN"=
 id=3D"ref-for-dfn-coded-frame-3">coded frame</a>. For video and text, the =
duration indicates how long
            the video frame or text <em class=3D"rfc2119">SHOULD</em> be di=
splayed. For audio, the duration represents the sum
            of all the samples contained within the coded frame. For exampl=
e, if an audio frame
            contained 441 samples @44100Hz the frame duration would be 10 m=
illiseconds.
          </p>
        </dd>
        <dt>
          <dfn id=3D"dfn-coded-frame-end-timestamp" tabindex=3D"0" aria-has=
popup=3D"dialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">Coded Frame End Timestamp</dfn>
        </dt>
        <dd>
          <p>
            The sum of a <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"http=
s://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-coded-frame" class=3D"internalDFN" id=
=3D"ref-for-dfn-coded-frame-4">coded frame</a> <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abs=
tract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#presentation-timestam=
p" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-presentation-timestamp-4">presentati=
on timestamp</a> and its <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"http=
s://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-coded-frame-duration" class=3D"internal=
DFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-coded-frame-duration-2">coded frame duration</a>. It=
 represents the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.g=
ithub.io/media-source/#presentation-timestamp" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"=
ref-for-presentation-timestamp-5">presentation timestamp</a> that immediate=
ly follows the
            coded frame.
          </p>
        </dd>
        <dt>
          <dfn id=3D"dfn-coded-frame-group" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D=
"dialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">Coded Frame Group</dfn>
        </dt>
        <dd>
          <p>
            A group of <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https:=
//w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-coded-frame" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"=
ref-for-dfn-coded-frame-5">coded frames</a> that are adjacent and have mono=
tonically increasing
            <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.githu=
b.io/media-source/#dfn-decode-timestamp" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-fo=
r-dfn-decode-timestamp-2">decode timestamps</a> without any gaps. Discontin=
uities detected by the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https:=
//w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-coded-frame-processing" class=3D"internal=
DFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-coded-frame-processing-1">coded frame processing</a>=
 algorithm and <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"abort()" href=3D"https:=
//w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-sourcebuffer-abort" class=3D"internalDFN"=
 id=3D"ref-for-dom-sourcebuffer-abort-1"><code>abort</code></a><code>()</co=
de> calls trigger the start of a new
            coded frame group.
          </p>
        </dd>
        <dt>
          <dfn data-plurals=3D"decode timestamps" id=3D"dfn-decode-timestam=
p" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">Decode Tim=
estamp</dfn>
        </dt>
        <dd>
          <p>
            The decode timestamp indicates the latest time at which the fra=
me needs to be decoded
            assuming instantaneous decoding and rendering of this and any d=
ependant frames (this is
            equal to the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"http=
s://w3c.github.io/media-source/#presentation-timestamp" class=3D"internalDF=
N" id=3D"ref-for-presentation-timestamp-6">presentation timestamp</a> of th=
e earliest frame, in <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://=
w3c.github.io/media-source/#presentation-order" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D=
"ref-for-presentation-order-1">presentation order</a>, that is dependant on=
 this frame). If frames can be decoded out of
            <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.githu=
b.io/media-source/#presentation-order" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-=
presentation-order-2">presentation order</a>, then the decode timestamp <em=
 class=3D"rfc2119">MUST</em> be present in or derivable from
            the byte stream. The user agent <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST</em>=
 run the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.i=
o/media-source/#dfn-append-error" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-a=
ppend-error-1">append error</a> algorithm if this is not
            the case. If frames cannot be decoded out of <a data-link-type=
=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#presentati=
on-order" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-presentation-order-3">present=
ation order</a> and a decode
            timestamp is not present in the byte stream, then the decode ti=
mestamp is equal to the
            <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.githu=
b.io/media-source/#presentation-timestamp" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-=
for-presentation-timestamp-7">presentation timestamp</a>.
          </p>
        </dd>
        <dt>
          <dfn class=3D"export" data-export=3D"" data-plurals=3D"initializa=
tion segments" id=3D"dfn-initialization-segment" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspop=
up=3D"dialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">Initialization Segment</dfn>
        </dt>
        <dd>
          <p>
            A sequence of bytes that contain all of the initialization info=
rmation required to
            decode a sequence of <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=
=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-media-segment" class=3D"interna=
lDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-media-segment-1">media segments</a>. This includes =
codec initialization data,
            <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.githu=
b.io/media-source/#dfn-track-id" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-tr=
ack-id-1">Track ID</a> mappings for multiplexed segments, and timestamp off=
sets (e.g., edit
            lists).
          </p>
          <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-generated=
ID"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note" aria-le=
vel=3D"3"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
            The <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.g=
ithub.io/media-source/#byte-stream-format-specs" class=3D"internalDFN" id=
=3D"ref-for-byte-stream-format-specs-1">byte stream format specifications</=
a> in the byte stream format registry
            [<cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"ht=
tps://w3c.github.io/media-source/#bib-mse-registry" title=3D"Media Source E=
xtensions=E2=84=A2 Byte Stream Format Registry">MSE-REGISTRY</a></cite>] co=
ntain format specific examples.
          </p></div>
        </dd>
        <dt>
          <dfn class=3D"export" data-export=3D"" data-plurals=3D"media segm=
ents" id=3D"dfn-media-segment" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog" data=
-dfn-type=3D"dfn">Media Segment</dfn>
        </dt>
        <dd>
          <p>
            A sequence of bytes that contain packetized &amp; timestamped m=
edia data for a portion of
            the <a href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.htm=
l#media-timeline">media timeline</a>. Media segments are always associated =
with the most
            recently appended <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D=
"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-initialization-segment" class=3D"i=
nternalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-initialization-segment-1">initialization segm=
ent</a>.
          </p>
          <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-generated=
ID-0"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-0" ari=
a-level=3D"3"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
            The <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.g=
ithub.io/media-source/#byte-stream-format-specs" class=3D"internalDFN" id=
=3D"ref-for-byte-stream-format-specs-2">byte stream format specifications</=
a> in the byte stream format registry
            [<cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"ht=
tps://w3c.github.io/media-source/#bib-mse-registry" title=3D"Media Source E=
xtensions=E2=84=A2 Byte Stream Format Registry">MSE-REGISTRY</a></cite>] co=
ntain format specific examples.
          </p></div>
        </dd>
        <dt>
          <dfn id=3D"mediasource-object-url" data-plurals=3D"mediasource ob=
ject urls" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">Me=
diaSource object URL</dfn>
        </dt>
        <dd>
          <p>
            A <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSource" href=3D"htt=
ps://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource" class=3D"internalDFN" id=
=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource-2"><code>MediaSource</code></a> object URL is a=
 unique <a data-link-type=3D"dfn" href=3D"https://www.w3.org/TR/FileAPI/#bl=
ob-url">blob URL</a> created by
            <a data-link-type=3D"method" data-lt=3D"createObjectURL()" href=
=3D"https://www.w3.org/TR/FileAPI/#dfn-createObjectURL"><code>createObjectU=
RL</code></a><code>()</code>. It is used to attach a <a data-link-type=3D"i=
dl" data-lt=3D"MediaSource" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom=
-mediasource" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource-3"><code>=
MediaSource</code></a> object to an
            HTMLMediaElement.
          </p>
          <p>
            These URLs are the same as a <a data-link-type=3D"dfn" href=3D"=
https://www.w3.org/TR/FileAPI/#blob-url">blob URLs</a>, except that anythin=
g in the definition of
            that feature that refers to <a data-link-type=3D"interface" dat=
a-lt=3D"File" href=3D"https://www.w3.org/TR/FileAPI/#dfn-file"><code>File</=
code></a> and <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"Blob" href=3D"http=
s://www.w3.org/TR/FileAPI/#dfn-Blob"><code>Blob</code></a> objects is hereb=
y extended to also
            apply to <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSource" href=
=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource" class=3D"internalD=
FN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource-4"><code>MediaSource</code></a> objects.
          </p>
          <p>
            The <a data-link-type=3D"dfn" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.=
org/multipage/browsers.html#concept-origin">origin</a> of the MediaSource o=
bject URL is the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg=
.org/multipage/webappapis.html#relevant-settings-object">relevant settings =
object</a> of
            <a data-link-type=3D"dfn" href=3D"https://webidl.spec.whatwg.or=
g/#this">this</a> during the call to <a data-link-type=3D"method" data-lt=
=3D"createObjectURL()" href=3D"https://www.w3.org/TR/FileAPI/#dfn-createObj=
ectURL"><code>createObjectURL</code></a><code>()</code>.
          </p>
          <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-generated=
ID-1"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-1" ari=
a-level=3D"3"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
            For example, the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn" href=3D"https://html=
.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/browsers.html#concept-origin">origin</a> of the =
MediaSource object URL affects the way that the
            media element is <a href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multip=
age/canvas.html#security-with-canvas-elements">consumed
            by canvas</a>.
          </p></div>
        </dd>
        <dt>
          <dfn id=3D"parent-media-source" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"d=
ialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">Parent Media Source</dfn>
        </dt>
        <dd>
          <p>
            The parent media source of a <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=
=3D"SourceBuffer" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-sourcebuf=
fer" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-sourcebuffer-6"><code>SourceBu=
ffer</code></a> object is the <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSou=
rce" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource" class=3D"=
internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource-5"><code>MediaSource</code></a> =
object that
            created it.
          </p>
        </dd>
        <dt>
          <dfn id=3D"presentation-start-time" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=
=3D"dialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">Presentation Start Time</dfn>
        </dt>
        <dd>
          <p>
            The presentation start time is the earliest time point in the p=
resentation and
            specifies the initial <a href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/m=
ultipage/media.html#">playback
            position</a> and <a href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multip=
age/media.html#">earliest possible
            position</a>. All presentations created using this specificatio=
n have a presentation
            start time of 0.
          </p>
          <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-generated=
ID-2"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-2" ari=
a-level=3D"3"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
            For the purposes of determining if <a data-link-type=3D"interfa=
ce" data-lt=3D"HTMLMediaElement" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multi=
page/media.html#htmlmediaelement"><code>HTMLMediaElement</code></a>'s <a da=
ta-link-type=3D"attribute" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/m=
edia.html#dom-media-buffered"><code>buffered</code></a>
            contains a <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"TimeRange=
s" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#timeranges"><c=
ode>TimeRanges</code></a> that includes the current playback position, impl=
ementations
            <em class=3D"rfc2119">MAY</em> choose to allow a current playba=
ck position at or after <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https=
://w3c.github.io/media-source/#presentation-start-time" class=3D"internalDF=
N" id=3D"ref-for-presentation-start-time-1">presentation start time</a>
            and before the first <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D=
"TimeRanges" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#time=
ranges"><code>TimeRanges</code></a> to play the first <a data-link-type=3D"=
interface" data-lt=3D"TimeRanges" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/mult=
ipage/media.html#timeranges"><code>TimeRanges</code></a> if that
            <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"TimeRanges" href=3D"=
https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#timeranges"><code>TimeRan=
ges</code></a> starts within a reasonably short time, like 1 second, after
            <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.githu=
b.io/media-source/#presentation-start-time" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref=
-for-presentation-start-time-2">presentation start time</a>. This allowance=
 accommodates the reality that muxed streams
            commonly do not begin all tracks precisely at <a data-link-type=
=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#presentati=
on-start-time" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-presentation-start-time-=
3">presentation start time</a>.
            Implementations <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST</em> report the actu=
al buffered range, regardless of this allowance.
          </p></div>
        </dd>
        <dt>
          <dfn id=3D"presentation-interval" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D=
"dialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">Presentation Interval</dfn>
        </dt>
        <dd>
          <p>
            The presentation interval of a <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstrac=
t-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-coded-frame" class=3D=
"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-coded-frame-6">coded frame</a> is the time =
interval from its
            <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.githu=
b.io/media-source/#presentation-timestamp" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-=
for-presentation-timestamp-8">presentation timestamp</a> to the <a data-lin=
k-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#pres=
entation-timestamp" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-presentation-timest=
amp-9">presentation timestamp</a> plus the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstrac=
t-op" data-lt=3D"coded frame duration" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-=
source/#dfn-coded-frame-duration" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-c=
oded-frame-duration-3">coded frame's duration</a>. For example, if a coded =
frame has a presentation
            timestamp of 10 seconds and a <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract=
-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-coded-frame-duration" =
class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-coded-frame-duration-4">coded frame=
 duration</a> of 100 milliseconds, then the
            presentation interval would be [10-10.1). Note that the start o=
f the range is
            inclusive, but the end of the range is exclusive.
          </p>
        </dd>
        <dt>
          <dfn id=3D"presentation-order" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"di=
alog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">Presentation Order</dfn>
        </dt>
        <dd>
          <p>
            The order that <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"ht=
tps://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-coded-frame" class=3D"internalDFN" id=
=3D"ref-for-dfn-coded-frame-7">coded frames</a> are rendered in the present=
ation. The presentation
            order is achieved by ordering <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract=
-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-coded-frame" class=3D"=
internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-coded-frame-8">coded frames</a> in monotonic=
ally increasing order by
            their <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c=
.github.io/media-source/#presentation-timestamp" class=3D"internalDFN" id=
=3D"ref-for-presentation-timestamp-10">presentation timestamps</a>.
          </p>
        </dd>
        <dt>
          <dfn id=3D"presentation-timestamp" data-export=3D"" data-plurals=
=3D"presentation timestamps" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog" data-d=
fn-type=3D"dfn">Presentation Timestamp</dfn>
        </dt>
        <dd>
          <p>
            A reference to a specific time in the presentation. The present=
ation timestamp in a
            <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.githu=
b.io/media-source/#dfn-coded-frame" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn=
-coded-frame-9">coded frame</a> indicates when the frame <em class=3D"rfc21=
19">SHOULD</em> be rendered.
          </p>
        </dd>
        <dt>
          <dfn id=3D"random-access-point" data-export=3D"" tabindex=3D"0" a=
ria-haspopup=3D"dialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">Random Access Point</dfn>
        </dt>
        <dd>
          <p>
            A position in a <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"h=
ttps://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-media-segment" class=3D"internalDFN"=
 id=3D"ref-for-dfn-media-segment-2">media segment</a> where decoding and co=
ntinuous playback can begin
            without relying on any previous data in the segment. For video =
this tends to be the
            location of I-frames. In the case of audio, most audio frames c=
an be treated as a
            random access point. Since video tracks tend to have a more spa=
rse distribution of
            random access points, the location of these points are usually =
considered the random
            access points for multiplexed streams.
          </p>
        </dd>
        <dt>
          <dfn id=3D"dfn-sourcebuffer-byte-stream-format-specification" tab=
index=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">SourceBuffer byt=
e stream format specification</dfn>
        </dt>
        <dd>
          <p>
            The specific <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"http=
s://w3c.github.io/media-source/#byte-stream-format-specs" class=3D"internal=
DFN" id=3D"ref-for-byte-stream-format-specs-3">byte stream format specifica=
tion</a> that describes the format of the byte
            stream accepted by a <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"Sourc=
eBuffer" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-sourcebuffer" clas=
s=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-sourcebuffer-7"><code>SourceBuffer</cod=
e></a> instance. The <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://=
w3c.github.io/media-source/#byte-stream-format-specs" class=3D"internalDFN"=
 id=3D"ref-for-byte-stream-format-specs-4">byte stream format specification=
</a>, for a <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"SourceBuffer" href=3D"http=
s://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-sourcebuffer" class=3D"internalDFN" id=
=3D"ref-for-dom-sourcebuffer-8"><code>SourceBuffer</code></a> object, is in=
itially selected based on the
            <var data-type=3D"DOMString">type</var> passed to the <a data-l=
ink-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"addSourceBuffer()" href=3D"https://w3c.github.i=
o/media-source/#dom-mediasource-addsourcebuffer" class=3D"internalDFN" id=
=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource-addsourcebuffer-1"><code>addSourceBuffer</code>=
</a><code>()</code> call that created the
            object, and can be updated by <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=
=3D"changeType()" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-sourcebuf=
fer-changetype" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-sourcebuffer-change=
type-2"><code>changeType</code></a><code>()</code> calls on the object.
          </p>
        </dd>
        <dt>
          <dfn id=3D"dfn-sourcebuffer-configuration" tabindex=3D"0" aria-ha=
spopup=3D"dialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn"><code>SourceBuffer</code> configura=
tion</dfn>
        </dt>
        <dd>
          <p>
            A specific set of tracks distributed across one or more <a data=
-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"SourceBuffer" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/m=
edia-source/#dom-sourcebuffer" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-sour=
cebuffer-9"><code>SourceBuffer</code></a> objects owned
            by a single <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSource" h=
ref=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource" class=3D"intern=
alDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource-6"><code>MediaSource</code></a> instan=
ce.
          </p>
          <p>
            Implementations <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST</em> support at leas=
t 1 <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSource" href=3D"https://w3c.g=
ithub.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for=
-dom-mediasource-7"><code>MediaSource</code></a> object with the following
            configurations:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>A single SourceBuffer with 1 audio track and/or 1 video tra=
ck.
            </li>
            <li>Two SourceBuffers with one handling a single audio track an=
d the other handling a
            single video track.
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            MediaSource objects <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST</em> support eac=
h of the configurations above, but they are only
            required to support one configuration at a time. Supporting mul=
tiple configurations at
            once or additional configurations is a quality of implementatio=
n issue.
          </p>
        </dd>
        <dt>
          <dfn data-plurals=3D"track descriptions" id=3D"dfn-track-descript=
ion" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">Track De=
scription</dfn>
        </dt>
        <dd>
          <p>
            A byte stream format specific structure that provides the <a da=
ta-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source=
/#dfn-track-id" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-track-id-2">Track I=
D</a>, codec
            configuration, and other metadata for a single track. Each trac=
k description inside a
            single <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3=
c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-initialization-segment" class=3D"internalDFN"=
 id=3D"ref-for-dfn-initialization-segment-2">initialization segment</a> has=
 a unique <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.=
io/media-source/#dfn-track-id" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-trac=
k-id-3">Track ID</a>. The user agent <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST</em> run
            the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.g=
ithub.io/media-source/#dfn-append-error" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-fo=
r-dfn-append-error-2">append error</a> algorithm if the <a data-link-type=
=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-track-=
id" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-track-id-4">Track ID</a> is not=
 unique within the
            <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.githu=
b.io/media-source/#dfn-initialization-segment" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"=
ref-for-dfn-initialization-segment-3">initialization segment</a>.
          </p>
        </dd>
        <dt>
          <dfn data-plurals=3D"track ids" id=3D"dfn-track-id" tabindex=3D"0=
" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">Track ID</dfn>
        </dt>
        <dd>
          <p>
            A Track ID is a byte stream format specific identifier that mar=
ks sections of the byte
            stream as being part of a specific track. The Track ID in a <a =
data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-sour=
ce/#dfn-track-description" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-track-de=
scription-1">track description</a>
            identifies which sections of a <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstrac=
t-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-media-segment" class=
=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-media-segment-3">media segment</a> belon=
g to that track.
          </p>
        </dd>
      </dl>
    </section>
    <section id=3D"mediasource" data-dfn-for=3D"MediaSource"><div class=3D"=
header-wrapper"><h2 id=3D"x3-mediasource-interface"><bdi class=3D"secno">3.=
 </bdi>
        <dfn data-export=3D"" data-dfn-type=3D"interface" id=3D"dom-mediaso=
urce" data-idl=3D"interface" data-title=3D"MediaSource" data-dfn-for=3D"" t=
abindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog"><code>MediaSource</code></dfn> inter=
face
      </h2><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-sourc=
e/#mediasource" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 3."></a></div>
     =20
      <p>
        The <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSource" href=3D"https=
://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D=
"ref-for-dom-mediasource-8"><code>MediaSource</code></a> interface represen=
ts a source of media data for an
        <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"HTMLMediaElement" href=
=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#htmlmediaelement"><co=
de>HTMLMediaElement</code></a>. It keeps track of the <a data-link-type=3D"=
idl" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource-readystate=
" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource-readystate-1"><code>r=
eadyState</code></a> for this source as
        well as a list of <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#do=
m-sourcebuffer" class=3D"internalDFN" data-link-type=3D"idl" id=3D"ref-for-=
dom-sourcebuffer-10"><code>SourceBuffer</code></a> objects that can be used=
 to add media data to the
        presentation. MediaSource objects are created by the web applicatio=
n and then attached to
        an HTMLMediaElement. The application uses the <a href=3D"https://w3=
c.github.io/media-source/#dom-sourcebuffer" class=3D"internalDFN" data-link=
-type=3D"idl" id=3D"ref-for-dom-sourcebuffer-11"><code>SourceBuffer</code><=
/a> objects in
        <a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-sourc=
e/#dom-mediasource-sourcebuffers" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-m=
ediasource-sourcebuffers-1"><code>sourceBuffers</code></a> to add media dat=
a to this source. The HTMLMediaElement
        fetches this media data from the <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/m=
edia-source/#dom-mediasource" class=3D"internalDFN" data-link-type=3D"idl" =
id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource-9"><code>MediaSource</code></a> object when i=
t is needed during
        playback.
      </p>
      <p>
        Each <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSource" href=3D"http=
s://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource" class=3D"internalDFN" id=
=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource-10"><code>MediaSource</code></a> object has a <=
dfn data-dfn-for=3D"MediaSource" data-idl=3D"" data-noexport=3D"" data-dfn-=
type=3D"attribute" id=3D"dfn-live-seekable-range" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspo=
pup=3D"dialog">[[live seekable
        range]]</dfn> internal slot that stores a <a href=3D"https://html.s=
pec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#normalised-timeranges-object">normalize=
d TimeRanges object</a>. It
        is initialized to an empty <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=
=3D"TimeRanges" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#t=
imeranges"><code>TimeRanges</code></a> object when the <a data-link-type=3D=
"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSource" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#d=
om-mediasource" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource-11"><co=
de>MediaSource</code></a> object is
        created, is maintained by <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"setL=
iveSeekableRange()" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediaso=
urce-setliveseekablerange" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasou=
rce-setliveseekablerange-1"><code>setLiveSeekableRange</code></a><code>()</=
code> and
        <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"clearLiveSeekableRange()" href=
=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource-clearliveseekablera=
nge" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource-clearliveseekabler=
ange-1"><code>clearLiveSeekableRange</code></a><code>()</code>, and is used=
 in <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#htmlmediaelement-extensi=
ons" data-matched-text=3D"[[[#htmlmediaelement-extensions]]]" class=3D"sec-=
ref"><bdi class=3D"secno">10. </bdi>
        HTMLMediaElement Extensions</a>
        to modify <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"HTMLMediaEleme=
nt" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#htmlmediaelem=
ent"><code>HTMLMediaElement</code></a>'s <a data-link-type=3D"attribute" hr=
ef=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#dom-media-seekable"=
><code>seekable</code></a> behavior.
      </p>
      <p>
        Each <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSource" href=3D"http=
s://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource" class=3D"internalDFN" id=
=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource-12"><code>MediaSource</code></a> object has a <=
dfn data-dfn-for=3D"MediaSource" data-idl=3D"" data-noexport=3D"" data-dfn-=
type=3D"attribute" id=3D"dfn-has-ever-been-attached" tabindex=3D"0" aria-ha=
spopup=3D"dialog">[[has ever been
        attached]]</dfn> internal slot that stores a <a data-link-type=3D"i=
nterface" data-lt=3D"boolean" href=3D"https://webidl.spec.whatwg.org/#idl-b=
oolean"><code>boolean</code></a>. It is initialized to false when
        the <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSource" href=3D"https=
://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D=
"ref-for-dom-mediasource-13"><code>MediaSource</code></a> object is created=
, and is set true in the extended
        <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"HTMLMediaElement" href=
=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#htmlmediaelement"><co=
de>HTMLMediaElement</code></a>'s <a data-link-type=3D"dfn" href=3D"https://=
html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#concept-media-load-resource">reso=
urce fetch algorithm</a> as described in the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstr=
act-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-attaching-to-a-medi=
a-element" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-attaching-to-a-media-ele=
ment-1">attaching to a media element</a> algorithm. The extended <a data-li=
nk-type=3D"dfn" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#c=
oncept-media-load-resource">resource fetch algorithm</a> uses this internal
        slot to conditionally fail attachment of a <a data-link-type=3D"idl=
" data-lt=3D"MediaSource" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-m=
ediasource" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource-14"><code>M=
ediaSource</code></a> using a <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSou=
rceHandle" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasourcehandl=
e" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasourcehandle-1"><code>Media=
SourceHandle</code></a>
        set on a <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"HTMLMediaElemen=
t" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#htmlmediaeleme=
nt"><code>HTMLMediaElement</code></a>'s <a data-link-type=3D"attribute" hre=
f=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#dom-media-srcobject"=
><code>srcObject</code></a> attribute.
      </p>
      <pre class=3D"idl def" id=3D"webidl-26865842"><span class=3D"idlHeade=
r"><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#webid=
l-26865842">WebIDL</a></span><code><span data-idl=3D"" class=3D"idlEnum" id=
=3D"idl-def-readystate" data-title=3D"ReadyState">enum <dfn data-export=3D"=
