diaSource.isTypeSupported()|isTypeSupported" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=
=3D"dialog"><code>isTypeSupported()</code></dfn> method
      </h3><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-sourc=
e/#istypesupported-method" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 3.12"></a></=
div>
      <p>
        Check to see whether the <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-sou=
rce/#dom-mediasource" class=3D"internalDFN" data-link-type=3D"idl" id=3D"re=
f-for-dom-mediasource-35"><code>MediaSource</code></a> is capable of creati=
ng <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-sourcebuffer" class=
=3D"internalDFN" data-link-type=3D"idl" id=3D"ref-for-dom-sourcebuffer-24">=
<code>SourceBuffer</code></a>
        objects for the specified MIME type.
      </p>
     =20
      <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-generatedID-1=
7"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-17" aria-=
level=3D"3"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
        If true is returned from this method, it only indicates that the <a=
 data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSource" href=3D"https://w3c.github.=
io/media-source/#dom-mediasource" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-m=
ediasource-36"><code>MediaSource</code></a>
        implementation is capable of creating <a data-link-type=3D"idl" dat=
a-lt=3D"SourceBuffer" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-sourc=
ebuffer" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-sourcebuffer-25"><code>Sou=
rceBuffer</code></a> objects for the specified MIME type.
        An <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"addSourceBuffer()" href=3D"=
https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource-addsourcebuffer" class=
=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource-addsourcebuffer-4"><code>add=
SourceBuffer</code></a><code>()</code> call <em class=3D"rfc2119">SHOULD</e=
m> still fail if sufficient resources are not
        available to support the addition of a new <a data-link-type=3D"idl=
" data-lt=3D"SourceBuffer" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-=
sourcebuffer" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-sourcebuffer-26"><cod=
e>SourceBuffer</code></a>.
      </p></div>
      <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-generatedID-1=
8"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-18" aria-=
level=3D"3"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
        This method returning true implies that <a data-link-type=3D"interf=
ace" data-lt=3D"HTMLMediaElement" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/mult=
ipage/media.html#htmlmediaelement"><code>HTMLMediaElement</code></a>'s
        <a data-link-type=3D"method" data-lt=3D"canPlayType()" href=3D"http=
s://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#dom-navigator-canplaytype"><c=
ode>canPlayType</code></a><code>()</code> will return "maybe" or "probably"=
 since it does not make
        sense for a <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSource" href=
=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource" class=3D"internalD=
FN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource-37"><code>MediaSource</code></a> to suppo=
rt a type the HTMLMediaElement knows it cannot play.
      </p></div>
      <p>When this method is invoked, the user agent must run the following=
 steps:</p><ol class=3D"method-algorithm">
        <li>If <var data-type=3D"DOMString">type</var> is an empty string, =
then return false.
        </li>
        <li>If <var data-type=3D"DOMString">type</var> does not contain a v=
alid MIME type string, then return false.
        </li>
        <li>If <var data-type=3D"DOMString">type</var> contains a media typ=
e or media subtype that the MediaSource does not support,
        then return false.
        </li>
        <li>If <var data-type=3D"DOMString">type</var> contains a codec tha=
t the MediaSource does not support, then return false.
        </li>
        <li>If the MediaSource does not support the specified combination o=
f media type, media
        subtype, and codecs then return false.
        </li>
        <li>Return true.
        </li>
      </ol></section><section id=3D"mediasource-events"><div class=3D"heade=
