      <section id=3D"mediasource-in-worker-communication-model"><div class=
=3D"header-wrapper"><h3 id=3D"x3-14-cross-context-communication-model"><bdi=
 class=3D"secno">3.14 </bdi>
          <dfn id=3D"dfn-cross-context-communication-model" tabindex=3D"0" =
aria-haspopup=3D"dialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">Cross-context communication =
model</dfn>
        </h3><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-sou=
rce/#mediasource-in-worker-communication-model" aria-label=3D"Permalink for=
 Section 3.14"></a></div>
       =20
        <p>
          When a <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"Window" href=3D=
"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/nav-history-apis.html#window"><code=
>Window</code></a> <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"HTMLMediaElem=
ent" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#htmlmediaele=
ment"><code>HTMLMediaElement</code></a> is attached to a <a data-link-type=
=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope" href=3D"https://html.=
spec.whatwg.org/multipage/workers.html#dedicatedworkerglobalscope"><code>De=
dicatedWorkerGlobalScope</code></a>
          <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSource" href=3D"https:/=
/w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"r=
ef-for-dom-mediasource-41"><code>MediaSource</code></a>, each context has a=
lgorithms that depend on information from the other.
        </p>
        <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-generatedID=
-19"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-19" ari=
a-level=3D"4"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
          <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"HTMLMediaElement" href=
=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#htmlmediaelement"><co=
de>HTMLMediaElement</code></a> is exposed only to <a data-link-type=3D"inte=
rface" data-lt=3D"Window" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/na=
v-history-apis.html#window"><code>Window</code></a> contexts, but <a data-l=
ink-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSource" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/medi=
a-source/#dom-mediasource" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasou=
rce-42"><code>MediaSource</code></a> and
          related objects defined in this specification are exposed in <a d=
ata-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"Window" href=3D"https://html.spec.wh=
atwg.org/multipage/nav-history-apis.html#window"><code>Window</code></a> an=
d
          <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"DedicatedWorkerGlobalS=
cope" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/workers.html#dedicated=
workerglobalscope"><code>DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope</code></a> contexts. Th=
is lets applications construct a
          <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSource" href=3D"https:/=
/w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"r=
ef-for-dom-mediasource-43"><code>MediaSource</code></a> object in either of=
 those types of context and attach it to an
          <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"HTMLMediaElement" href=
=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#htmlmediaelement"><co=
de>HTMLMediaElement</code></a> object in a <a data-link-type=3D"interface" =
data-lt=3D"Window" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/nav-histo=
ry-apis.html#window"><code>Window</code></a> context using a <a data-link-t=
ype=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#mediaso=
urce-object-url" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-mediasource-object-url=
-1">MediaSource object URL</a> or
          a <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSourceHandle" href=3D=
"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasourcehandle" class=3D"intern=
alDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasourcehandle-5"><code>MediaSourceHandle</code=
></a> as described in the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"htt=
ps://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-attaching-to-a-media-element" class=3D=
"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-attaching-to-a-media-element-2">attaching t=
o a media element</a> algorithm. A
          <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSource" href=3D"https:/=
/w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"r=
ef-for-dom-mediasource-44"><code>MediaSource</code></a> object is not <a da=
ta-link-type=3D"extended-attribute" data-lt=3D"Transferable" href=3D"https:=
//html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/structured-data.html#transferable"><code>T=
ransferable</code></a>; it is only visible in the context where
          it was created.
        </p></div>
        <p>
          The rest of this section describes a model for bounding informati=
on latency for
          attachments of a <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"Windo=
w" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/nav-history-apis.html#win=
dow"><code>Window</code></a> media element to a <a data-link-type=3D"interf=
ace" data-lt=3D"DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatw=
g.org/multipage/workers.html#dedicatedworkerglobalscope"><code>DedicatedWor=
kerGlobalScope</code></a>
          <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSource" href=3D"https:/=
/w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"r=
ef-for-dom-mediasource-45"><code>MediaSource</code></a>. While the model de=
scribes communication using message passing,
          implementations <em class=3D"rfc2119">MAY</em> choose to communic=
ate in potentially faster ways, such as using
          shared memory and locks. Attachments to a <a data-link-type=3D"in=
terface" data-lt=3D"Window" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/=
nav-history-apis.html#window"><code>Window</code></a> <a data-link-type=3D"=
idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSource" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#do=
m-mediasource" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource-46"><cod=
e>MediaSource</code></a> synchronously have
          the information already without communicating it across contexts.
        </p>
        <p>
          A <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSource" href=3D"https=
://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D=
"ref-for-dom-mediasource-47"><code>MediaSource</code></a> that is construct=
ed in a <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"DedicatedWorkerGlobalSco=
pe" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/workers.html#dedicatedwo=
rkerglobalscope"><code>DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope</code></a> has a
          <dfn data-dfn-for=3D"MediaSource" data-idl=3D"" data-noexport=3D"=
" data-dfn-type=3D"attribute" id=3D"dfn-port-to-main" tabindex=3D"0" aria-h=
aspopup=3D"dialog">[[port to main]]</dfn> internal slot that stores a
          <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"MessagePort" href=3D"h=
ttps://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/web-messaging.html#messageport"><code=
>MessagePort</code></a> setup during attachment and nulled during detachmen=
t. A <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"Window" href=3D"https://htm=
l.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/nav-history-apis.html#window"><code>Window</cod=
e></a>
          <a data-link-type=3D"attribute" data-lt=3D"[[port to main]]" href=
=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-port-to-main" class=3D"internal=
DFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-port-to-main-1"><code>[[port to main]]</code></a> is=
 always null.
        </p>
        <p>
          An <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"HTMLMediaElement" h=
ref=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#htmlmediaelement">=
<code>HTMLMediaElement</code></a> extended by this specification and attach=
ed to a
          <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"DedicatedWorkerGlobalS=
cope" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/workers.html#dedicated=
workerglobalscope"><code>DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope</code></a> <a data-link=
-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSource" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-s=
ource/#dom-mediasource" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource=
-48"><code>MediaSource</code></a> similarly has a <dfn data-dfn-for=3D"HTML=
MediaElement" data-idl=3D"" data-noexport=3D"" data-dfn-type=3D"attribute" =
id=3D"dfn-port-to-worker" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog">[[port to=
 worker]]</dfn> internal slot that stores a <a data-link-type=3D"interface"=
 data-lt=3D"MessagePort" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/web=
-messaging.html#messageport"><code>MessagePort</code></a>
          and a <dfn data-dfn-for=3D"HTMLMediaElement" data-idl=3D"" data-n=
oexport=3D"" data-dfn-type=3D"attribute" id=3D"dfn-channel-with-worker" tab=
index=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog">[[channel with worker]]</dfn> internal=
 slot
          that stores a <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"MessageC=
hannel" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/web-messaging.html#m=
essagechannel"><code>MessageChannel</code></a>, both setup during attachmen=
t and nulled during
          detachment. Both <a data-link-type=3D"attribute" data-lt=3D"[[por=
t to worker]]" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-port-to-work=
er" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-port-to-worker-1"><code>[[port =
to worker]]</code></a> and <a data-link-type=3D"attribute" data-lt=3D"[[cha=
nnel with worker]]" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-channel=
-with-worker" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-channel-with-worker-1=
"><code>[[channel with worker]]</code></a> are null unless attached to a <a=
 data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope" href=
=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/workers.html#dedicatedworkerglob=
alscope"><code>DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope</code></a>
          <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSource" href=3D"https:/=
/w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"r=
ef-for-dom-mediasource-49"><code>MediaSource</code></a>.
        </p>
        <p>
          Algorithms in this specification that need to communicate informa=
tion from a <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"Window" href=3D"http=
s://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/nav-history-apis.html#window"><code>Wind=
ow</code></a>
          <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"HTMLMediaElement" href=
=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#htmlmediaelement"><co=
de>HTMLMediaElement</code></a> to an attached <a data-link-type=3D"interfac=
e" data-lt=3D"DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.=
org/multipage/workers.html#dedicatedworkerglobalscope"><code>DedicatedWorke=
rGlobalScope</code></a> <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSource" h=
ref=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource" class=3D"intern=
alDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource-50"><code>MediaSource</code></a>, or
          vice versa, will use these internal ports implicitly to post a me=
ssage to their
          counterpart, where the implicit handler of the message runs steps=
 as described in the
          algorithms.
        </p>
      </section>
      <section id=3D"mediasource-algorithms"><div class=3D"header-wrapper">=
<h3 id=3D"x3-15-algorithms"><bdi class=3D"secno">3.15 </bdi>
          Algorithms
        </h3><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-sou=
rce/#mediasource-algorithms" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 3.15"></a>=
</div>
       =20
        <section id=3D"mediasource-attach"><div class=3D"header-wrapper"><h=
4 id=3D"x3-15-1-attaching-to-a-media-element"><bdi class=3D"secno">3.15.1 <=
/bdi>
            <dfn id=3D"dfn-attaching-to-a-media-element" tabindex=3D"0" ari=
a-haspopup=3D"dialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">Attaching to a media element</d=
fn>
          </h4><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-s=
ource/#mediasource-attach" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 3.15.1"></a>=
</div>
         =20
          <p>
            There are distinct mechanisms for attaching a <a data-link-type=
=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSource" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source=
/#dom-mediasource" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource-51">=
<code>MediaSource</code></a> to a media element
            depending on where the <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"Med=
iaSource" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource" clas=
s=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource-52"><code>MediaSource</code=
></a> object was constructed, in a <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=
=3D"Window" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/nav-history-apis=
.html#window"><code>Window</code></a> versus
            in a <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"DedicatedWorker=
GlobalScope" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/workers.html#de=
dicatedworkerglobalscope"><code>DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope</code></a>:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <p>
                Attaching a <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSourc=
e" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource" class=3D"in=
ternalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource-53"><code>MediaSource</code></a> t=
hat was constructed in a <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"Window"=
 href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/nav-history-apis.html#windo=
w"><code>Window</code></a> can be done by
                assigning a <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"h=
ttps://w3c.github.io/media-source/#mediasource-object-url" class=3D"interna=
lDFN" id=3D"ref-for-mediasource-object-url-2">MediaSource object URL</a> fo=
r that <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSource" href=3D"https://w3=
c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-=
for-dom-mediasource-54"><code>MediaSource</code></a> to the media
                element <a data-link-type=3D"attribute" href=3D"https://htm=
l.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#dom-media-src"><code>src</code></a> =
attribute or the src attribute of a &lt;source&gt;
                inside a media element. A <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract=
-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#mediasource-object-url" cl=
ass=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-mediasource-object-url-3">MediaSource obj=
ect URL</a> is created by passing a
                MediaSource object to <a data-link-type=3D"method" data-lt=
=3D"createObjectURL()" href=3D"https://www.w3.org/TR/FileAPI/#dfn-createObj=
ectURL"><code>createObjectURL</code></a><code>()</code>.
              </p>
              <p>
                Though implementations <em class=3D"rfc2119">MAY</em> allow=
 <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-=
source/#mediasource-object-url" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-mediaso=
urce-object-url-4">MediaSource object URL</a> creation in a
                <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"DedicatedWorkerG=
lobalScope" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/workers.html#ded=
icatedworkerglobalscope"><code>DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope</code></a> for a =
<a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSource" href=3D"https://w3c.githu=
b.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom=
-mediasource-55"><code>MediaSource</code></a> constructed in that worker,
                attempting to use that <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op=
" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#mediasource-object-url" class=
=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-mediasource-object-url-5">MediaSource object=
 URL</a> to attach to a media element
                using either the <a data-link-type=3D"attribute" href=3D"ht=
tps://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#dom-media-src"><code>src</c=
ode></a> attribute or the src attribute of a
                &lt;source&gt; inside a media element <em class=3D"rfc2119"=
>MUST</em> fail in the media element's <a data-link-type=3D"dfn" href=3D"ht=
tps://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#concept-media-load-resource=
">resource fetch algorithm</a>, as extended below.
              </p>
              <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-gener=
atedID-20"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-2=
0" aria-level=3D"5"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
                Extending the object URL attachment mechanism to worker Med=
iaSource object URLs
                would further propagate this idiom that is less preferred v=
ersus using srcObject,
                and would unnecessarily increase user agent interoperabilit=
y risk and
                implementation complexity.
              </p></div>
            </li>
