https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource" class=3D"internalDFN" =
id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource-60"><code>MediaSource</code></a> object is us=
ed as the media provider object and current media
            resource in the local mode logic in the <a data-link-type=3D"df=
n" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#concept-media-=
load-resource">resource fetch algorithm</a>. This also means
            that the remote mode logic that includes observance of any prel=
oad attribute is skipped
            when a MediaSource object is attached. Even with that eventual =
change to [<cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"http=
s://w3c.github.io/media-source/#bib-html" title=3D"HTML Standard">HTML</a><=
/cite>], the
            execution of the following steps at the beginning of the local =
mode logic is still
            required when the current media resource is a <a data-link-type=
=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSource" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source=
/#dom-mediasource" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource-61">=
<code>MediaSource</code></a> object.
