e/media.html#concept-media-load-resource">resource fetch algorithm</a>, exe=
cute the additional steps, below.
          </p>
          <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-generated=
ID-22"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-22" a=
ria-level=3D"5"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
            Relative to the action which triggered the media element's reso=
urce selection
            algorithm, these steps are asynchronous. The <a data-link-type=
=3D"dfn" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#concept-=
media-load-resource">resource fetch algorithm</a> is run after
            the task that invoked the resource selection algorithm is allow=
ed to continue and a
            stable state is reached. Implementations may delay the steps in=
 the "<i>Otherwise</i>"
            clause, below, until the MediaSource object is ready for use.
          </p></div>
