h4 id=3D"x3-15-3-seeking"><bdi class=3D"secno">3.15.3 </bdi>
            <dfn id=3D"dfn-seeking" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog"=
 data-dfn-type=3D"dfn" class=3D"respec-offending-element" title=3D"Found de=
finition for &quot;Seeking&quot;, but nothing links to it. This is usually =
a spec bug!">Seeking</dfn>
          </h4><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-s=
ource/#mediasource-seeking" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 3.15.3"></a=
></div>
         =20
          <p>
            Run the following steps as part of the "<i>Wait until the user =
agent has established
            whether or not the media data for the new playback position is =
available, and, if it
            is, until it has decoded enough data to play back that position=
"</i> step of the
            <a href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#do=
m-media-seek">seek algorithm</a>:
          </p>
          <ol>
            <li>
              <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-gener=
atedID-27"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-2=
7" aria-level=3D"5"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
                The media element looks for <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstra=
ct-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-media-segment" class=
=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-media-segment-4">media segments</a> cont=
aining the <var data-type=3D"double">new playback
                position</var> in each <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D=
"SourceBuffer" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-sourcebuffer=
" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-sourcebuffer-29"><code>SourceBuff=
er</code></a> object in
                <a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/med=
ia-source/#dom-mediasource-activesourcebuffers" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D=
"ref-for-dom-mediasource-activesourcebuffers-9"><code>activeSourceBuffers</=
code></a>. Any position within a <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D=
"TimeRanges" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#time=
ranges"><code>TimeRanges</code></a> in the
                current value of the <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-l=
t=3D"HTMLMediaElement" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media=
.html#htmlmediaelement"><code>HTMLMediaElement</code></a>'s <a data-link-ty=
pe=3D"attribute" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#=
dom-media-buffered"><code>buffered</code></a> attribute
                has all necessary media segments buffered for that position=
.
              </p></div>
              <dl class=3D"switch">
                <dt>
                  If <var>new playback position</var> is not in any <a data=
-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"TimeRanges" href=3D"https://html.spec.w=
hatwg.org/multipage/media.html#timeranges"><code>TimeRanges</code></a> of <=
a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"HTMLMediaElement" href=3D"https:/=
/html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#htmlmediaelement"><code>HTMLMedi=
aElement</code></a>'s
                  <a data-link-type=3D"attribute" href=3D"https://html.spec=
.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#dom-media-buffered"><code>buffered</code><=
/a>
                </dt>
                <dd>
                  <ol>
                    <li>If the <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"H=
TMLMediaElement" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#=
htmlmediaelement"><code>HTMLMediaElement</code></a>'s <a data-link-type=3D"=
idl" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-readystate" class=3D"i=
nternalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-readystate-2"><code>readyState</code></a> att=
ribute is
                    greater than <a data-link-type=3D"const" href=3D"https:=
//html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#dom-media-have_metadata"><code>=
HAVE_METADATA</code></a>, then set the
                    <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"HTMLMediaEle=
ment" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#htmlmediael=
ement"><code>HTMLMediaElement</code></a>'s <a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=
=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-readystate" class=3D"internalDF=
N" id=3D"ref-for-dom-readystate-3"><code>readyState</code></a> attribute to
                    <a data-link-type=3D"const" href=3D"https://html.spec.w=
hatwg.org/multipage/media.html#dom-media-have_metadata"><code>HAVE_METADATA=
</code></a>.
                      <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-contain=
er-generatedID-28"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"=
h-note-28" aria-level=3D"5"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
                        Per <code><a href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/m=
ultipage/media.html#ready-states">HTMLMediaElement ready states</a></code> =
[<cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://w3c.gi=
thub.io/media-source/#bib-html" title=3D"HTML Standard">HTML</a></cite>] lo=
gic, <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"HTMLMediaElement" href=3D"h=
ttps://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#htmlmediaelement"><code>HT=
MLMediaElement</code></a>'s
                        <a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=3D"https://w3c.githu=
b.io/media-source/#dom-readystate" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-=
readystate-4"><code>readyState</code></a> changes may trigger events on the
                        HTMLMediaElement.
                      </p></div>
                    </li>
                    <li>The media element waits until an <a data-link-type=
=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"appendBuffer()" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-sou=
rce/#dom-sourcebuffer-appendbuffer" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom=
-sourcebuffer-appendbuffer-3"><code>appendBuffer</code></a><code>()</code> =
call
                    causes the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=
=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-coded-frame-processing" class=
=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-coded-frame-processing-2">coded frame pr=
ocessing</a> algorithm to set the
                    <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"HTMLMediaEle=
ment" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#htmlmediael=
ement"><code>HTMLMediaElement</code></a>'s <a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=
=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-readystate" class=3D"internalDF=
N" id=3D"ref-for-dom-readystate-5"><code>readyState</code></a> attribute to=
 a value
                    greater than <a data-link-type=3D"const" href=3D"https:=
//html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#dom-media-have_metadata"><code>=
HAVE_METADATA</code></a>.
                      <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-contain=
er-generatedID-29"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"=
h-note-29" aria-level=3D"5"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
                        The web application can use <a data-link-type=3D"id=
l" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-sourcebuffer-buffered" c=
lass=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-sourcebuffer-buffered-1"><code>buffe=
red</code></a> and
                        <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"HTMLMedi=
aElement" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#htmlmed=
iaelement"><code>HTMLMediaElement</code></a>'s <a data-link-type=3D"attribu=
te" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#dom-media-buf=
fered"><code>buffered</code></a> to determine what the
                        media element needs to resume playback.
                      </p></div>
                    </li>
                  </ol>
                </dd>
                <dt>
                  Otherwise
                </dt>
                <dd>
                  Continue
                  <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-g=
eneratedID-30"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-no=
te-30" aria-level=3D"5"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
                    If the <a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=3D"https://w3c.gi=
thub.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource-readystate" class=3D"internalDFN" id=
=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource-readystate-20"><code>readyState</code></a> attr=
ibute is "<a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-sou=
rce/#dom-readystate-ended" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-readysta=
te-ended-5"><code>ended</code></a>" and the
                    <var>new playback position</var> is within a <a data-li=
nk-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"TimeRanges" href=3D"https://html.spec.what=
wg.org/multipage/media.html#timeranges"><code>TimeRanges</code></a> current=
ly in
                    <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"HTMLMediaEle=
ment" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#htmlmediael=
ement"><code>HTMLMediaElement</code></a>'s <a data-link-type=3D"attribute" =
href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#dom-media-buffere=
d"><code>buffered</code></a>, then the seek operation
                    must continue to completion here even if one or more cu=
rrently selected or
                    enabled track buffers' largest range end timestamp is l=
ess than <var>new playback
                    position</var>. This condition should only occur due to=
 logic in
                    <a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io=
/media-source/#dom-sourcebuffer-buffered" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-f=
or-dom-sourcebuffer-buffered-2"><code>buffered</code></a> when <a data-link=
-type=3D"idl" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource-r=
eadystate" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource-readystate-2=
1"><code>readyState</code></a> is
                    "<a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=3D"https://w3c.github.i=
o/media-source/#dom-readystate-ended" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-d=
om-readystate-ended-6"><code>ended</code></a>".
                  </p></div>
                </dd>
              </dl>
            </li>
            <li>The media element resets all decoders and initializes each =
one with data from the
            appropriate <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https=
://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-initialization-segment" class=3D"interna=
lDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-initialization-segment-4">initialization segment</a=
>.
            </li>
            <li>The media element feeds <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-o=
p" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-coded-frame" class=3D"in=
ternalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-coded-frame-10">coded frames</a> from the <a d=
ata-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-sourc=
e/#dfn-active-track-buffers" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-active=
-track-buffers-1">active track buffers</a> into the
            decoders starting with the closest <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abs=
tract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#random-access-point" =
class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-random-access-point-1">random access po=
int</a> before the <var>new playback
            position</var>.
            </li>
            <li>Resume the <a href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipag=
e/media.html#dom-media-seek">seek algorithm</a> at the "<i>Await a stable s=
tate</i>"
            step.
            </li>
          </ol>
        </section>
        <section id=3D"buffer-monitoring"><div class=3D"header-wrapper"><h4=
 id=3D"x3-15-4-sourcebuffer-monitoring"><bdi class=3D"secno">3.15.4 </bdi>
            <dfn id=3D"dfn-sourcebuffer-monitoring" tabindex=3D"0" aria-has=
popup=3D"dialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">SourceBuffer Monitoring</dfn>
          </h4><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-s=
ource/#buffer-monitoring" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 3.15.4"></a><=
/div>
         =20
          <p>
            The following steps are periodically run during playback to mak=
e sure that all of the
            <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"SourceBuffer" href=3D"http=
s://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-sourcebuffer" class=3D"internalDFN" id=
=3D"ref-for-dom-sourcebuffer-30"><code>SourceBuffer</code></a> objects in <=
a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-me=
diasource-activesourcebuffers" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-medi=
asource-activesourcebuffers-10"><code>activeSourceBuffers</code></a> have <=
a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-so=
urce/#enough-data" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-enough-data-1">enoug=
h data to ensure uninterrupted playback</a>. Changes to <a data-link-type=
=3D"idl" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource-active=
sourcebuffers" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource-activeso=
urcebuffers-11"><code>activeSourceBuffers</code></a> also
            cause these steps to run because they affect the conditions tha=
t trigger state
            transitions.
          </p>
          <p>
            Having <dfn id=3D"enough-data" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"=
dialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">enough data to ensure uninterrupted playback<=
/dfn> is an
            implementation specific condition where the user agent determin=
es that it currently has
            enough data to play the presentation without stalling for a mea=
ningful period of time.
            This condition is constantly evaluated to determine when to tra=
nsition the media
            element into and out of the <a data-link-type=3D"const" href=3D=
"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#dom-media-have_enough_da=
ta"><code>HAVE_ENOUGH_DATA</code></a> ready state. These
            transitions indicate when the user agent believes it has enough=
 data buffered or it
            needs more data respectively.
          </p>
          <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-generated=
ID-31"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-31" a=
ria-level=3D"5"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
            An implementation <em class=3D"rfc2119">MAY</em> choose to use =
bytes buffered, time buffered, the append rate, or
            any other metric it sees fit to determine when it has enough da=
ta. The metrics used <em class=3D"rfc2119">MAY</em>
            change during playback so web applications <em class=3D"rfc2119=
">SHOULD</em> only rely on the value of
            <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"HTMLMediaElement" hr=
ef=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#htmlmediaelement"><=
code>HTMLMediaElement</code></a>'s <a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=3D"https:=
//w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-readystate" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"r=
ef-for-dom-readystate-6"><code>readyState</code></a> to determine whether m=
ore data
            is needed or not.
          </p></div>
          <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-generated=
ID-32"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-32" a=
ria-level=3D"5"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
            When the media element needs more data, the user agent <em clas=
s=3D"rfc2119">SHOULD</em> transition it from
            <a data-link-type=3D"const" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.or=
g/multipage/media.html#dom-media-have_enough_data"><code>HAVE_ENOUGH_DATA</=
code></a> to <a data-link-type=3D"const" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.o=
rg/multipage/media.html#dom-media-have_future_data"><code>HAVE_FUTURE_DATA<=
/code></a> early
            enough for a web application to be able to respond without caus=
ing an interruption in
            playback. For example, transitioning when the current playback =
position is 500ms before
            the end of the buffered data gives the application roughly 500m=
s to append more data
            before playback stalls.
          </p></div>
          <dl class=3D"switch">
            <dt>
              If the <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"HTMLMediaEl=
ement" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#htmlmediae=
lement"><code>HTMLMediaElement</code></a>'s <a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=
=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-readystate" class=3D"internalDF=
N" id=3D"ref-for-dom-readystate-7"><code>readyState</code></a> attribute eq=
uals
              <a data-link-type=3D"const" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.=
org/multipage/media.html#dom-media-have_nothing"><code>HAVE_NOTHING</code><=
/a>:
            </dt>
            <dd>
              <ol>
                <li>Abort these steps.
                </li>
              </ol>
            </dd>
            <dt>
              If <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"HTMLMediaElemen=
t" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#htmlmediaeleme=
nt"><code>HTMLMediaElement</code></a>'s <a data-link-type=3D"attribute" hre=
f=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#dom-media-buffered">=
<code>buffered</code></a> does not contain a
              <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"TimeRanges" href=
=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#timeranges"><code>Tim=
eRanges</code></a> for the current playback position:
            </dt>
            <dd>
              <ol>
                <li>Set the <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"HTML=
MediaElement" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#htm=
lmediaelement"><code>HTMLMediaElement</code></a>'s <a data-link-type=3D"idl=
" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-readystate" class=3D"inte=
rnalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-readystate-8"><code>readyState</code></a> attrib=
ute to
                <a data-link-type=3D"const" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatw=
g.org/multipage/media.html#dom-media-have_metadata"><code>HAVE_METADATA</co=
de></a>.
                  <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-g=
eneratedID-33"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-no=
te-33" aria-level=3D"5"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
                    Per <code><a href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multi=
page/media.html#ready-states">HTMLMediaElement ready states</a></code> [<ci=
te><a class=3D"bibref" data-link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://w3c.github=
.io/media-source/#bib-html" title=3D"HTML Standard">HTML</a></cite>] logic,=
 <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"HTMLMediaElement" href=3D"https=
://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#htmlmediaelement"><code>HTMLMe=
diaElement</code></a>'s
                    <a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io=
/media-source/#dom-readystate" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-read=
ystate-9"><code>readyState</code></a> changes may trigger events on the
                    HTMLMediaElement.
                  </p></div>
                </li>
                <li>Abort these steps.
                </li>
              </ol>
            </dd>
            <dt>
              If <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"HTMLMediaElemen=
t" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#htmlmediaeleme=
nt"><code>HTMLMediaElement</code></a>'s <a data-link-type=3D"attribute" hre=
f=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#dom-media-buffered">=
<code>buffered</code></a> contains a <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-l=
t=3D"TimeRanges" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#=
timeranges"><code>TimeRanges</code></a>
              that includes the current playback position and <a data-link-=
type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#enough=
-data" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-enough-data-2">enough data to en=
sure uninterrupted playback</a>:
            </dt>
            <dd>
              <ol>
                <li>Set the <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"HTML=
MediaElement" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#htm=
lmediaelement"><code>HTMLMediaElement</code></a>'s <a data-link-type=3D"idl=
" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-readystate" class=3D"inte=
rnalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-readystate-10"><code>readyState</code></a> attri=
bute to
                <a data-link-type=3D"const" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatw=
g.org/multipage/media.html#dom-media-have_enough_data"><code>HAVE_ENOUGH_DA=
TA</code></a>.
                  <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-g=
eneratedID-34"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-no=
te-34" aria-level=3D"5"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
                    Per <code><a href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multi=
page/media.html#ready-states">HTMLMediaElement ready states</a></code> [<ci=
te><a class=3D"bibref" data-link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://w3c.github=
.io/media-source/#bib-html" title=3D"HTML Standard">HTML</a></cite>] logic,=
 <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"HTMLMediaElement" href=3D"https=
://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#htmlmediaelement"><code>HTMLMe=
diaElement</code></a>'s
                    <a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io=
/media-source/#dom-readystate" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-read=
ystate-11"><code>readyState</code></a> changes may trigger events on the
                    HTMLMediaElement.
                  </p></div>
                </li>
                <li>Playback may resume at this point if it was previously =
suspended by a
