                </li>
                <li><a data-link-type=3D"dfn" href=3D"https://html.spec.wha=
twg.org/multipage/webappapis.html#queue-a-task">Queue a task</a> to <a data=
-link-type=3D"dfn" href=3D"https://dom.spec.whatwg.org/#concept-event-fire"=
>fire an event</a> named <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"addsourcebuff=
er" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-addsourcebuffer" class=
=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-addsourcebuffer-4"><code>addsourcebuffer=
</code></a> at
                <a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/med=
ia-source/#dom-mediasource-activesourcebuffers" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D=
"ref-for-dom-mediasource-activesourcebuffers-27"><code>activeSourceBuffers<=
/code></a>
                </li>
              </ol>
            </dd>
          </dl>
        </section>
        <section id=3D"duration-change-algorithm"><div class=3D"header-wrap=
per"><h4 id=3D"x3-15-6-duration-change"><bdi class=3D"secno">3.15.6 </bdi>
            <dfn id=3D"dfn-duration-change" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D=
"dialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">Duration change</dfn>
          </h4><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-s=
ource/#duration-change-algorithm" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 3.15.=
6"></a></div>
         =20
          <p>
            Follow these steps when <a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=3D"https=
://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource-duration" class=3D"internalD=
FN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource-duration-3"><code>duration</code></a> nee=
ds to change to a <var data-type=3D"unrestricted double">new
            duration</var>.
          </p>
          <ol>
            <li>If the current value of <a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=3D"h=
ttps://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource-duration" class=3D"inter=
nalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource-duration-4"><code>duration</code></a>=
 is equal to <var>new duration</var>, then
            return.
            </li>
            <li>If <var>new duration</var> is less than the highest <a data=
-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#=
presentation-timestamp" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-presentation-ti=
mestamp-11">presentation timestamp</a> of any
            buffered <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://=
w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-coded-frame" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"re=
f-for-dfn-coded-frame-11">coded frames</a> for all <a data-link-type=3D"idl=
" data-lt=3D"SourceBuffer" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-=
sourcebuffer" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-sourcebuffer-43"><cod=
e>SourceBuffer</code></a> objects in
            <a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-s=
ource/#dom-mediasource-sourcebuffers" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-d=
om-mediasource-sourcebuffers-18"><code>sourceBuffers</code></a>, then throw=
 an <a data-link-type=3D"exception" data-lt=3D"InvalidStateError" href=3D"h=
ttps://webidl.spec.whatwg.org/#invalidstateerror"><code>InvalidStateError</=
code></a> exception and abort
            these steps.
              <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-gener=
atedID-37"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-3=
7" aria-level=3D"5"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
                Duration reductions that would truncate currently buffered =
media are disallowed.
                When truncation is necessary, use <a data-link-type=3D"idl"=
 data-lt=3D"remove()" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-sourc=
ebuffer-remove" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-sourcebuffer-remove=
-1"><code>remove</code></a><code>()</code> to reduce the buffered
                range before updating <a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=3D"htt=
ps://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource-duration" class=3D"interna=
lDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource-duration-5"><code>duration</code></a>.
              </p></div>
            </li>
            <li>Let <var data-type=3D"unrestricted double">highest end time=
</var> be the largest <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https:/=
/w3c.github.io/media-source/#track-buffer-ranges" class=3D"internalDFN" id=
=3D"ref-for-track-buffer-ranges-1">track buffer ranges</a>
            end time across all the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" h=
ref=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#track-buffer" class=3D"internalD=
FN" id=3D"ref-for-track-buffer-2">track buffers</a> across all <a data-link=
-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"SourceBuffer" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-=
source/#dom-sourcebuffer" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-sourcebuf=
fer-44"><code>SourceBuffer</code></a> objects in
            <a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-s=
ource/#dom-mediasource-sourcebuffers" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-d=
om-mediasource-sourcebuffers-19"><code>sourceBuffers</code></a>.
            </li>
            <li>If <var>new duration</var> is less than <var data-type=3D"u=
nrestricted double">highest end time</var>, then
              <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-gener=
atedID-38"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-3=
8" aria-level=3D"5"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
                This condition can occur because the <a data-link-type=3D"d=
fn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-coded-frame=
-removal" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-coded-frame-removal-1">co=
ded frame removal</a> algorithm preserves
                coded frames that start before the start of the removal ran=
ge.
              </p></div>
              <ol>
                <li>Update <var>new duration</var> to equal <var data-type=
=3D"unrestricted double">highest end time</var>.
                </li>
              </ol>
            </li>
            <li>Update <a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=3D"https://w3c.github=
.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource-duration" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref=
-for-dom-mediasource-duration-6"><code>duration</code></a> to <var>new dura=
tion</var>.
            </li>
            <li>Use the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https=
://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-mirror-if-necessary" class=3D"internalDF=
N" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-mirror-if-necessary-4">mirror if necessary</a> algorit=
hm to run the following steps in <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D=
"Window" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/nav-history-apis.ht=
ml#window"><code>Window</code></a>
            to update the media element's duration:
              <ol>
                <li>Update the media element's <a data-link-type=3D"attribu=
te" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#dom-media-dur=
ation"><code>duration</code></a> to <var>new duration</var>.
                </li>
                <li>Run the <a href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipa=
ge/media.html#durationChange">HTMLMediaElement duration change algorithm</a=
>.
                </li>
              </ol>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </section>
        <section id=3D"end-of-stream-algorithm"><div class=3D"header-wrappe=
r"><h4 id=3D"x3-15-7-end-of-stream"><bdi class=3D"secno">3.15.7 </bdi>
            <dfn id=3D"dfn-end-of-stream" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"d=
ialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">End of stream</dfn>
          </h4><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-s=
ource/#end-of-stream-algorithm" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 3.15.7"=
></a></div>
         =20
          <p>
            This algorithm gets called when the application signals the end=
 of stream via an
            <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"endOfStream()" href=3D"htt=
ps://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource-endofstream" class=3D"inte=
rnalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource-endofstream-4"><code>endOfStream</co=
de></a><code>()</code> call or an algorithm needs to signal a decode error.=
 This
            algorithm takes an <var data-type=3D"EndOfStreamError">error</v=
ar> parameter that indicates whether an error
            will be signalled.
          </p>
          <ol>
            <li>Change the <a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=3D"https://w3c.gi=
thub.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource-readystate" class=3D"internalDFN" id=
=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource-readystate-22"><code>readyState</code></a> attr=
ibute value to "<a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/med=
ia-source/#dom-readystate-ended" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-re=
adystate-ended-7"><code>ended</code></a>".
            </li>
            <li><a data-link-type=3D"dfn" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.=
org/multipage/webappapis.html#queue-a-task">Queue a task</a> to <a data-lin=
k-type=3D"dfn" href=3D"https://dom.spec.whatwg.org/#concept-event-fire">fir=
e an event</a> named <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"sourceended" href=
=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-sourceended" class=3D"internalD=
FN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-sourceended-1"><code>sourceended</code></a> at the <a=
 data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSource" href=3D"https://w3c.github.=
io/media-source/#dom-mediasource" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-m=
ediasource-87"><code>MediaSource</code></a>.
            </li>
            <li>
              <dl class=3D"switch">
                <dt>
                  If <var data-type=3D"EndOfStreamError">error</var> is not=
 set
                </dt>
                <dd>
                  <ol>
                    <li>Run the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=
=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-duration-change" class=3D"inter=
nalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-duration-change-3">duration change</a> algorithm =
with <var data-type=3D"unrestricted
                    double">new duration</var> set to the largest <a data-l=
ink-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#tr=
ack-buffer-ranges" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-track-buffer-ranges-=
2">track buffer ranges</a> end time across all the
                    <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w=
3c.github.io/media-source/#track-buffer" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-fo=
r-track-buffer-3">track buffers</a> across all <a data-link-type=3D"idl" da=
ta-lt=3D"SourceBuffer" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-sour=
cebuffer" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-sourcebuffer-45"><code>So=
urceBuffer</code></a> objects in
                    <a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io=
/media-source/#dom-mediasource-sourcebuffers" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"r=
ef-for-dom-mediasource-sourcebuffers-20"><code>sourceBuffers</code></a>.
                      <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-contain=
er-generatedID-39"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"=
h-note-39" aria-level=3D"5"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
                        This allows the duration to properly reflect the en=
d of the appended media
                        segments. For example, if the duration was explicit=
ly set to 10 seconds and
                        only media segments for 0 to 5 seconds were appende=
d before endOfStream()
                        was called, then the duration will get updated to 5=
 seconds.
                      </p></div>
                    </li>
                    <li>Notify the media element that it now has all of the=
 media data.
                    </li>
                  </ol>
                </dd>
                <dt>
                  If <var data-type=3D"EndOfStreamError">error</var> is set=
 to "<a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#=
dom-endofstreamerror-network" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-endof=
streamerror-network-2"><code>network</code></a>"
                </dt>
                <dd>
                  Use the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"htt=
ps://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-mirror-if-necessary" class=3D"internal=
DFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-mirror-if-necessary-5">mirror if necessary</a> algor=
ithm to run the following steps in
                  <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"Window" href=
=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/nav-history-apis.html#window"><c=
ode>Window</code></a>:
                  <dl class=3D"switch">
                    <dt>
                      If the <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"HTM=
LMediaElement" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#ht=
mlmediaelement"><code>HTMLMediaElement</code></a>'s <a data-link-type=3D"id=
l" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-readystate" class=3D"int=
ernalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-readystate-16"><code>readyState</code></a> attr=
ibute
                      equals <a data-link-type=3D"const" href=3D"https://ht=
ml.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#dom-media-have_nothing"><code>HAVE_=
NOTHING</code></a>
                    </dt>
                    <dd>
                      Run the <span>"<i>If the media data cannot be fetched=
 at all, due to network errors, causing the user agent to give up trying to=
 fetch the resource</i>"</span> steps of the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn" href=
=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#concept-media-load-re=
source">resource fetch algorithm</a>'s <a href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.=
org/multipage/media.html#media-data-processing-steps-list">media data proce=
ssing steps list</a>.
                    </dd>
                    <dt>
                      If the <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"HTM=
LMediaElement" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#ht=
mlmediaelement"><code>HTMLMediaElement</code></a>'s <a data-link-type=3D"id=
l" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-readystate" class=3D"int=
ernalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-readystate-17"><code>readyState</code></a> attr=
ibute is
                      greater than <a data-link-type=3D"const" href=3D"http=
s://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#dom-media-have_nothing"><code=
>HAVE_NOTHING</code></a>
                    </dt>
                    <dd>
                      Run the "<i>If the connection is interrupted after so=
me media data has been
                      received, causing the user agent to give up trying to=
 fetch the resource</i>"
                      steps of the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn" href=3D"https:=
//html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#concept-media-load-resource">re=
source fetch algorithm</a>'s <a href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multip=
age/media.html#media-data-processing-steps-list">media data processing step=
s list</a>.
                    </dd>
                  </dl>
                </dd>
                <dt>
                  If <var data-type=3D"EndOfStreamError">error</var> is set=
 to "<a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#=
dom-endofstreamerror-decode" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-endofs=
treamerror-decode-2"><code>decode</code></a>"
                </dt>
                <dd>
                  Use the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"htt=
ps://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-mirror-if-necessary" class=3D"internal=
DFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-mirror-if-necessary-6">mirror if necessary</a> algor=
ithm to run the following steps in
                  <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"Window" href=
=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/nav-history-apis.html#window"><c=
ode>Window</code></a>:
                  <dl class=3D"switch">
                    <dt>
                      If the <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"HTM=
LMediaElement" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#ht=
mlmediaelement"><code>HTMLMediaElement</code></a>'s <a data-link-type=3D"id=
l" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-readystate" class=3D"int=
ernalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-readystate-18"><code>readyState</code></a> attr=
ibute
                      equals <a data-link-type=3D"const" href=3D"https://ht=
ml.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#dom-media-have_nothing"><code>HAVE_=
NOTHING</code></a>
                    </dt>
                    <dd>
                      Run the "<i>If the media data can be fetched but is f=
ound by inspection to be
                      in an unsupported format, or can otherwise not be ren=
dered at all</i>" steps
                      of the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn" href=3D"https://html=
.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#concept-media-load-resource">resource=
 fetch algorithm</a>'s <a href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/me=
dia.html#media-data-processing-steps-list">media data processing steps list=
</a>.
                    </dd>
                    <dt>
                      If the <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"HTM=
LMediaElement" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#ht=
mlmediaelement"><code>HTMLMediaElement</code></a>'s <a data-link-type=3D"id=
l" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-readystate" class=3D"int=
ernalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-readystate-19"><code>readyState</code></a> attr=
ibute is
                      greater than <a data-link-type=3D"const" href=3D"http=
s://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#dom-media-have_nothing"><code=
>HAVE_NOTHING</code></a>
                    </dt>
                    <dd>
                      Run the <a href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multi=
page/media.html#fatal-decode-error">media data is corrupted</a> steps of th=
e <a data-link-type=3D"dfn" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/=
media.html#concept-media-load-resource">resource fetch algorithm</a>'s <a h=
ref=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#media-data-process=
ing-steps-list">media data processing steps list</a>.
                    </dd>
                  </dl>
                </dd>
              </dl>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </section>
        <section id=3D"mirror-if-necessary-algorithm"><div class=3D"header-=
wrapper"><h4 id=3D"x3-15-8-mirror-if-necessary"><bdi class=3D"secno">3.15.8=
 </bdi>
            <dfn id=3D"dfn-mirror-if-necessary" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopu=
p=3D"dialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">Mirror if necessary</dfn>
          </h4><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-s=
ource/#mirror-if-necessary-algorithm" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 3=
.15.8"></a></div>
         =20
          <p>
            This algorithm is used to run steps on <a data-link-type=3D"int=
erface" data-lt=3D"Window" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/n=
av-history-apis.html#window"><code>Window</code></a> from a <a data-link-ty=
pe=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSource" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-sour=
ce/#dom-mediasource" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource-88=
"><code>MediaSource</code></a> attached from
            either the same <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"Wind=
ow" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/nav-history-apis.html#wi=
ndow"><code>Window</code></a> or from a <a data-link-type=3D"interface" dat=
a-lt=3D"DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/mu=
ltipage/workers.html#dedicatedworkerglobalscope"><code>DedicatedWorkerGloba=
lScope</code></a>, usually to update
            the state of the attached <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-=
lt=3D"HTMLMediaElement" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/medi=
a.html#htmlmediaelement"><code>HTMLMediaElement</code></a>. This algorithm =
takes a <var>steps</var>
            parameter that lists the steps to run on <a data-link-type=3D"i=
nterface" data-lt=3D"Window" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage=
/nav-history-apis.html#window"><code>Window</code></a>.
          </p>
          <dl class=3D"switch">
            <dt>
              If the <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSource" href=
=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource" class=3D"internalD=
FN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource-89"><code>MediaSource</code></a> was cons=
tructed in a <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"DedicatedWorkerGlob=
alScope" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/workers.html#dedica=
tedworkerglobalscope"><code>DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope</code></a>:
            </dt>
            <dd>
              Post an internal <code>mirror on window</code> message to <a =
data-link-type=3D"attribute" data-lt=3D"[[port to main]]" href=3D"https://w=
3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-port-to-main" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"re=
f-for-dfn-port-to-main-6"><code>[[port to main]]</code></a> whose
              implicit handler in <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=
=3D"Window" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/nav-history-apis=
.html#window"><code>Window</code></a> will run <var>steps</var>. Return con=
trol to the caller without
              awaiting that handler's receipt of the message.
              <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-gener=
atedID-40"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-4=
0" aria-level=3D"5"><span>Note</span></div><div class=3D"">
                The purpose of the mirror message mechanism is to ensure th=
at:
                <ol>
                  <li><var>steps</var> run asynchronously as their own task=
 on <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"Window" href=3D"https://html=
.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/nav-history-apis.html#window"><code>Window</code=
></a> rather than these
                  <var>steps</var> somehow happening in the middle of some =
other <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"Window" href=3D"https://ht=
ml.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/nav-history-apis.html#window"><code>Window</co=
de></a> task's
                  execution, and
                  </li>
                  <li><var>steps</var> are run without blocking the synchro=
nous execution and return of this
                  algorithm on <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"D=
edicatedWorkerGlobalScope" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/w=
orkers.html#dedicatedworkerglobalscope"><code>DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope</c=
ode></a>.
                  </li>
                </ol>
              </div></div>
            </dd>
            <dt>
              Otherwise:
            </dt>
            <dd>
              Run <var>steps</var>.
            </dd>
          </dl>
        </section>
      </section>
    </section>
    <section id=3D"mediasourcehandle"><div class=3D"header-wrapper"><h2 id=
=3D"x4-mediasourcehandle-interface"><bdi class=3D"secno">4. </bdi>
        <dfn data-export=3D"" data-dfn-type=3D"interface" id=3D"dom-mediaso=
urcehandle" data-idl=3D"interface" data-title=3D"MediaSourceHandle" data-df=
n-for=3D"" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog"><code>MediaSourceHandle<=
/code></dfn> interface
      </h2><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-sourc=
e/#mediasourcehandle" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 4."></a></div>
     =20
      <p>
        The <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSourceHandle" href=3D=
"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasourcehandle" class=3D"intern=
alDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasourcehandle-13"><code>MediaSourceHandle</cod=
e></a> interface represents a proxy for a <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=
=3D"MediaSource" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasourc=
e" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource-90"><code>MediaSourc=
e</code></a> object that is
        useful for attaching a <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"D=
edicatedWorkerGlobalScope" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/w=
orkers.html#dedicatedworkerglobalscope"><code>DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope</c=
ode></a> <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSource" href=3D"https://=
w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"re=
f-for-dom-mediasource-91"><code>MediaSource</code></a> to a <a data-link-ty=
pe=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"Window" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/mu=
ltipage/nav-history-apis.html#window"><code>Window</code></a>
        <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"HTMLMediaElement" href=
=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#htmlmediaelement"><co=
de>HTMLMediaElement</code></a> using <a data-link-type=3D"attribute" href=
=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#dom-media-srcobject">=
<code>srcObject</code></a> as described in the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abs=
tract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-attaching-to-a-me=
dia-element" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-attaching-to-a-media-e=
lement-3">attaching to a media element</a> algorithm.
      </p>
      <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-generatedID-4=
1"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-41" aria-=
level=3D"3"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
        This distinct object is necessary to attach a cross-context <a data=
-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSource" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/me=
dia-source/#dom-mediasource" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-medias=
ource-92"><code>MediaSource</code></a> to a media
        element because <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSource" h=
ref=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource" class=3D"intern=
alDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource-93"><code>MediaSource</code></a> objec=
ts themselves are not transferable since they are
        event targets.
      </p></div>
      <p>
        Each <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSourceHandle" href=
=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasourcehandle" class=3D"int=
ernalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasourcehandle-14"><code>MediaSourceHandle</=
code></a> object has a <dfn data-dfn-for=3D"MediaSourceHandle" data-idl=3D"=
" data-noexport=3D"" data-dfn-type=3D"attribute" id=3D"dfn-has-ever-been-as=
signed-as-srcobject" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog">[[has ever
        been assigned as srcobject]]</dfn> internal slot that stores a <a d=
ata-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"boolean" href=3D"https://webidl.spec=
.whatwg.org/#idl-boolean"><code>boolean</code></a>. It is
        initialized to false when the <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"=
MediaSourceHandle" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasou=
rcehandle" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasourcehandle-15"><c=
ode>MediaSourceHandle</code></a> object is created, is set true in the
        extended <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"HTMLMediaElemen=
t" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#htmlmediaeleme=
nt"><code>HTMLMediaElement</code></a>'s <a data-link-type=3D"attribute" hre=
f=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#dom-media-srcobject"=
><code>srcObject</code></a> setter as described in
        section <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#htmlmediaele=
ment-extensions" data-matched-text=3D"[[[#htmlmediaelement-extensions]]]" c=
lass=3D"sec-ref"><bdi class=3D"secno">10. </bdi>
        HTMLMediaElement Extensions</a>, and if true, prevents successful t=
ransfer of
        the <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSourceHandle" href=3D=
"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasourcehandle" class=3D"intern=
alDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasourcehandle-16"><code>MediaSourceHandle</cod=
e></a> as described in section <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-sourc=
e/#transfer" data-matched-text=3D"[[[#transfer]]]" class=3D"sec-ref"><bdi c=
lass=3D"secno">4.1 </bdi>
          Transfer</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSourceHandle" href=3D"htt=
ps://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasourcehandle" class=3D"internalDF=
N" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasourcehandle-17"><code>MediaSourceHandle</code></=
a> objects are <a data-link-type=3D"extended-attribute" data-lt=3D"Transfer=
able" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/structured-data.html#t=
ransferable"><code>Transferable</code></a>, each having a <dfn data-dfn-for=
=3D"MediaSourceHandle" data-idl=3D"" data-noexport=3D"" data-dfn-type=3D"at=
tribute" id=3D"dfn-detached" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog">[[Deta=
ched]]</dfn> internal slot that is used to ensure that once the
        handle object instance has been transferred, that instance cannot b=
e transferred again.
      </p>
      <pre class=3D"idl def" id=3D"webidl-1737388085"><span class=3D"idlHea=
der"><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#web=
idl-1737388085">WebIDL</a></span><code><span data-idl=3D"" class=3D"idlInte=
rface" id=3D"idl-def-mediasourcehandle" data-title=3D"MediaSourceHandle">[<=
span class=3D"extAttr"><a data-link-type=3D"extended-attribute" href=3D"htt=
ps://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/structured-data.html#transferable">Tran=
sferable</a></span>, <span class=3D"extAttr"><a data-link-type=3D"extended-=
attribute" href=3D"https://webidl.spec.whatwg.org/#Exposed">Exposed</a>=3D(=
Window,DedicatedWorker)</span>]
interface <a class=3D"internalDFN idlID" data-link-type=3D"interface" href=
=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasourcehandle" id=3D"ref-fo=
r-dom-mediasourcehandle-18"><code>MediaSourceHandle</code></a> {};</span></=
code></pre>
      <section id=3D"transfer"><div class=3D"header-wrapper"><h3 id=3D"x4-1=
-transfer"><bdi class=3D"secno">4.1 </bdi>
          Transfer
        </h3><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-sou=
rce/#transfer" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 4.1"></a></div>
       =20
        <p>
          The <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSourceHandle" href=
=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasourcehandle" class=3D"int=
ernalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasourcehandle-19"><code>MediaSourceHandle</=
code></a> <a data-link-type=3D"dfn" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/mu=
ltipage/structured-data.html#transfer-steps">transfer steps</a> and <a data=
-link-type=3D"dfn" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/structure=
d-data.html#transfer-receiving-steps">transfer-receiving steps</a> require =
the
          implementation to maintain an implicit internal slot referencing =
the underlying
          <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSource" href=3D"https:/=
/w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"r=
ef-for-dom-mediasource-94"><code>MediaSource</code></a> to enable <a data-l=
ink-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#df=
n-attaching-to-a-media-element" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-att=
aching-to-a-media-element-4">attaching to a media element</a> using
          <a data-link-type=3D"attribute" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.=
org/multipage/media.html#dom-media-srcobject"><code>srcObject</code></a> an=
d consequent setup of an attachment's <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op"=
 href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-cross-context-communicatio=
n-model" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-cross-context-communicatio=
n-model-1">cross-context communication model</a>.
        </p>
        <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-generatedID=
-42"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-42" ari=
a-level=3D"4"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
          Implementors should be aware that assumption of "move" semantics =
implied by
          <a data-link-type=3D"extended-attribute" data-lt=3D"Transferable"=
 href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/structured-data.html#transf=
erable"><code>Transferable</code></a> is not always reality. For example, e=
xtensions or internal
          implementations of postMessage using broadcast may cause unintend=
ed multiple recipients
          of a transferred <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSource=
Handle" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasourcehandle" =
class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasourcehandle-20"><code>MediaSo=
urceHandle</code></a>. For this reason, implementations are guided to
          not resolve which potential clone of a transferred <a data-link-t=
ype=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSourceHandle" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/med=
ia-source/#dom-mediasourcehandle" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-m=
ediasourcehandle-21"><code>MediaSourceHandle</code></a> is still valid
          for attachment until and unless any handle for the underlying <a =
data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSource" href=3D"https://w3c.github.i=
o/media-source/#dom-mediasource" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-me=
diasource-95"><code>MediaSource</code></a> object is
          used in the asynchronous portion of the media element's resource =
selection algorithm.
          This is similar to the existing behavior for attachment via <a da=
ta-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source=
/#mediasource-object-url" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-mediasource-o=
bject-url-11">MediaSource object URLs</a>,
          which can be cloned easily, where such a URL is valid for at most=
 one attachment start
          (across all of its potentially many clones).
        </p></div>
        <p>
          Implementations <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST</em> support at most o=
ne attachment (load) via
          <a data-link-type=3D"attribute" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.=
org/multipage/media.html#dom-media-srcobject"><code>srcObject</code></a> ev=
er for the <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSource" href=3D"https:=
//w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"=
ref-for-dom-mediasource-96"><code>MediaSource</code></a> object underlying =
a
          <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSourceHandle" href=3D"h=
ttps://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasourcehandle" class=3D"internal=
DFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasourcehandle-22"><code>MediaSourceHandle</code>=
</a>, regardless of potential cloning of the <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data=
-lt=3D"MediaSourceHandle" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-m=
ediasourcehandle" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasourcehandle=
-23"><code>MediaSourceHandle</code></a> due
          to varying implementations of <a data-link-type=3D"extended-attri=
bute" data-lt=3D"Transferable" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipa=
ge/structured-data.html#transferable"><code>Transferable</code></a>.
        </p>
        <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-generatedID=
-43"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-43" ari=
a-level=3D"4"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
          See <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.git=
hub.io/media-source/#dfn-attaching-to-a-media-element" class=3D"internalDFN=
" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-attaching-to-a-media-element-5">attaching to a media el=
ement</a> for how this is enforced during the asynchronous
          portion of the media element's resource selection algorithm.
        </p></div>
        <p>
          <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSourceHandle" href=3D"h=
ttps://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasourcehandle" class=3D"internal=
DFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasourcehandle-24"><code>MediaSourceHandle</code>=
</a> is only exposed on <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"Window" =
href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/nav-history-apis.html#window=
"><code>Window</code></a> and <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"De=
dicatedWorkerGlobalScope" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/wo=
rkers.html#dedicatedworkerglobalscope"><code>DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope</co=
de></a>
          contexts, and cannot successfully transfer between different <a d=
ata-link-type=3D"dfn" href=3D"https://tc39.es/ecma262/multipage/executable-=
code-and-execution-contexts.html#sec-agent-clusters">agent clusters</a> [<c=
ite><a class=3D"bibref" data-link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://w3c.githu=
b.io/media-source/#bib-ecmascript" title=3D"ECMAScript Language Specificati=
on">ECMASCRIPT</a></cite>]. Transfer of a <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=
=3D"MediaSourceHandle" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-medi=
asourcehandle" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasourcehandle-25=
"><code>MediaSourceHandle</code></a> object can only succeed
          within the same <a data-link-type=3D"dfn" href=3D"https://tc39.es=
/ecma262/multipage/executable-code-and-execution-contexts.html#sec-agent-cl=
usters">agent cluster</a>.
        </p>
        <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-generatedID=
-44"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-44" ari=
a-level=3D"4"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
          For example, transfer of a <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"M=
ediaSourceHandle" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasour=
cehandle" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasourcehandle-26"><co=
de>MediaSourceHandle</code></a> object from either a <a data-link-type=3D"i=
nterface" data-lt=3D"Window" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage=
/nav-history-apis.html#window"><code>Window</code></a> or
          <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"DedicatedWorkerGlobalS=
cope" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/workers.html#dedicated=
workerglobalscope"><code>DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope</code></a> to either a =
SharedWorker or a ServiceWorker will not
          succeed. Developers should be aware of this difference versus <a =
data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-sour=
ce/#mediasource-object-url" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-mediasource=
-object-url-12">MediaSource object URLs</a>
          which are <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"DOMString" h=
ref=3D"https://webidl.spec.whatwg.org/#idl-DOMString"><code>DOMString</code=
></a>s that can be communicated many ways. Even so, <a data-link-type=3D"df=
n|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-attaching-to=
-a-media-element" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-attaching-to-a-me=
dia-element-6">attaching to a media element</a> using a <a data-link-type=
=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#mediasourc=
e-object-url" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-mediasource-object-url-13=
">MediaSource object URL</a> can only succeed for a <a data-link-type=3D"id=
l" data-lt=3D"MediaSource" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-=
mediasource" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource-97"><code>=
MediaSource</code></a>
          that was constructed in a <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=
=3D"Window" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/nav-history-apis=
.html#window"><code>Window</code></a> context. See also the integration of =
the
          <a data-link-type=3D"dfn" href=3D"https://tc39.es/ecma262/multipa=
ge/executable-code-and-execution-contexts.html#agent">agent</a> and <a data=
-link-type=3D"dfn" href=3D"https://tc39.es/ecma262/multipage/executable-cod=
e-and-execution-contexts.html#sec-agent-clusters">agent cluster</a> formali=
sms for Web Application APIs
          [<cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"http=
s://w3c.github.io/media-source/#bib-html" title=3D"HTML Standard">HTML</a><=
/cite>] where related concepts such as <a data-link-type=3D"dfn" href=3D"ht=
tps://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/webappapis.html#dedicated-worker-agent=
">dedicated worker agents</a> are defined.
        </p></div>
        <p>
          <a data-link-type=3D"dfn" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/mu=
ltipage/structured-data.html#transfer-steps">Transfer steps</a> for a <a da=
ta-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSourceHandle" href=3D"https://w3c.gith=
ub.io/media-source/#dom-mediasourcehandle" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-=
for-dom-mediasourcehandle-27"><code>MediaSourceHandle</code></a> object <em=
 class=3D"rfc2119">MUST</em> include the following step:
        </p>
        <ol>
          <li>If the <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSourceHandle=
" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasourcehandle" class=
=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasourcehandle-28"><code>MediaSourceH=
andle</code></a>'s <a data-link-type=3D"attribute" data-lt=3D"[[has ever be=
en assigned as srcobject]]" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn=
-has-ever-been-assigned-as-srcobject" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-d=
fn-has-ever-been-assigned-as-srcobject-1"><code>[[has ever been assigned as=
 srcobject]]</code></a> internal slot is true, then the <a data-link-type=
=3D"dfn" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/structured-data.htm=
l#transfer-steps">transfer steps</a> must fail by throwing a
          <a data-link-type=3D"exception" data-lt=3D"DataCloneError" href=
=3D"https://webidl.spec.whatwg.org/#datacloneerror"><code>DataCloneError</c=
ode></a> exception.
          </li>
        </ol>
      </section>
    </section>
    <section id=3D"sourcebuffer"><div class=3D"header-wrapper"><h2 id=3D"x5=
-sourcebuffer-interface"><bdi class=3D"secno">5. </bdi>
        <dfn data-export=3D"" data-dfn-type=3D"interface" id=3D"dom-sourceb=
uffer" data-idl=3D"interface" data-title=3D"SourceBuffer" data-dfn-for=3D""=
