for a <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/m=
edia-source/#random-access-point" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-rando=
m-access-point-2">random access point</a> <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract=
-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-coded-frame" class=3D"=
internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-coded-frame-20">coded frame</a>. The variabl=
e is initially set to true to indicate that <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstra=
ct-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#random-access-point" cla=
ss=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-random-access-point-3">random access point=
</a> <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/me=
dia-source/#dfn-coded-frame" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-coded-=
frame-21">coded frame</a> is needed before anything can be added to the <a =
data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-sour=
ce/#track-buffer" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-track-buffer-12">trac=
k buffer</a>.
        </p>
        <p>
          Each <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.gi=
thub.io/media-source/#track-buffer" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-tra=
ck-buffer-13">track buffer</a> has a <dfn id=3D"track-buffer-ranges" tabind=
ex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">track buffer ranges=
</dfn>
          variable that represents the presentation time ranges occupied by=
 the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/me=
dia-source/#dfn-coded-frame" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-coded-=
frame-22">coded frames</a>
          currently stored in the track buffer.
        </p>
        <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-generatedID=
-46"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-46" ari=
a-level=3D"4"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
          For track buffer ranges, these presentation time ranges are based=
 on <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/med=
ia-source/#presentation-timestamp" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-pres=
entation-timestamp-14">presentation timestamps</a>, frame durations, and po=
tentially coded frame group start times for coded
          frame groups across track buffers in a muxed <a data-link-type=3D=
"idl" data-lt=3D"SourceBuffer" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#=
dom-sourcebuffer" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-sourcebuffer-61">=
<code>SourceBuffer</code></a>.
        </p></div>
        <p>
          For specification purposes, this information is treated as if it =
were stored in a
          <a href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#norm=
alised-timeranges-object">normalized TimeRanges object</a>. Intersected <a =
data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-sour=
ce/#track-buffer-ranges" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-track-buffer-r=
anges-5">track buffer ranges</a> are
          used to report <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"HTMLMed=
iaElement" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#htmlme=
diaelement"><code>HTMLMediaElement</code></a>'s <a data-link-type=3D"attrib=
ute" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#dom-media-bu=
ffered"><code>buffered</code></a>, and <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST</em> ther=
efore
          support uninterrupted playback within each range of <a data-link-=
type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"HTMLMediaElement" href=3D"https://html.spec.w=
hatwg.org/multipage/media.html#htmlmediaelement"><code>HTMLMediaElement</co=
de></a>'s
          <a data-link-type=3D"attribute" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.=
org/multipage/media.html#dom-media-buffered"><code>buffered</code></a>.
        </p>
        <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-generatedID=
-47"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-47" ari=
a-level=3D"4"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
          These coded frame group start times differ slightly from those me=
ntioned in the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.gi=
thub.io/media-source/#dfn-coded-frame-processing" class=3D"internalDFN" id=
=3D"ref-for-dfn-coded-frame-processing-3">coded frame processing</a> algori=
thm in that they are the earliest <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" hre=
f=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#presentation-timestamp" class=3D"i=
nternalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-presentation-timestamp-15">presentation timestamp=
</a>
          across all track buffers following a discontinuity. Discontinuiti=
es can occur within the
          <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.=
io/media-source/#dfn-coded-frame-processing" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"re=
f-for-dfn-coded-frame-processing-4">coded frame processing</a> algorithm or=
 result from the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.=
github.io/media-source/#dfn-coded-frame-removal" class=3D"internalDFN" id=
=3D"ref-for-dfn-coded-frame-removal-2">coded frame removal</a>
          algorithm, regardless of <a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=3D"https:=
//w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-sourcebuffer-mode" class=3D"internalDFN" =
id=3D"ref-for-dom-sourcebuffer-mode-7"><code>mode</code></a>. The threshold=
 for determining
          disjointness of <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"htt=
ps://w3c.github.io/media-source/#track-buffer-ranges" class=3D"internalDFN"=
 id=3D"ref-for-track-buffer-ranges-6">track buffer ranges</a> is implementa=
tion-specific. For example, to
          reduce unexpected playback stalls, implementations <em class=3D"r=
fc2119">MAY</em> approximate the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=
=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-coded-frame-processing" class=
=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-coded-frame-processing-5">coded frame pr=
ocessing</a> algorithm's discontinuity detection logic by coalescing adjace=
nt ranges
          separated by a gap smaller than 2 times the maximum frame duratio=
n buffered so far in
          this <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.gi=
thub.io/media-source/#track-buffer" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-tra=
ck-buffer-14">track buffer</a>. Implementations <em class=3D"rfc2119">MAY</=
em> also use coded frame group start times as
          range start times across <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" hr=
ef=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#track-buffer" class=3D"internalDF=
N" id=3D"ref-for-track-buffer-15">track buffers</a> in a muxed <a data-link=
-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"SourceBuffer" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-=
source/#dom-sourcebuffer" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-sourcebuf=
fer-62"><code>SourceBuffer</code></a> to further reduce
          unexpected playback stalls.
        </p></div>
      </section>
