        <section id=3D"sourcebuffer-coded-frame-processing"><div class=3D"h=
eader-wrapper"><h4 id=3D"x5-5-8-coded-frame-processing"><bdi class=3D"secno=
">5.5.8 </bdi>
            <dfn data-export=3D"" id=3D"dfn-coded-frame-processing" tabinde=
x=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">Coded Frame Processi=
ng</dfn>
          </h4><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-s=
ource/#sourcebuffer-coded-frame-processing" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Sec=
tion 5.5.8"></a></div>
         =20
          <p>
            When complete <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"htt=
ps://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-coded-frame" class=3D"internalDFN" id=
=3D"ref-for-dfn-coded-frame-31">coded frames</a> have been parsed by the <a=
 data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-sou=
rce/#dfn-segment-parser-loop" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-segme=
nt-parser-loop-4">segment parser loop</a> then the
            following steps are run:
          </p>
          <ol>
            <li>
              <p>
                For each <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"http=
s://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-coded-frame" class=3D"internalDFN" id=
=3D"ref-for-dfn-coded-frame-32">coded frame</a> in the <a data-link-type=3D=
"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-media-seg=
ment" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-media-segment-13">media segme=
nt</a> run the following steps:
              </p>
              <ol>
                <li>
                  <i>Loop Top:</i>
                  <dl class=3D"switch">
                    <dt>
                      If <a data-link-type=3D"attribute" data-lt=3D"[[gener=
ate timestamps flag]]" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-gene=
rate-timestamps-flag" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-generate-time=
stamps-flag-6"><code>[[generate timestamps flag]]</code></a> equals true:
                    </dt>
                    <dd>
                      <ol>
                        <li>Let <var data-type=3D"double">presentation time=
stamp</var> equal 0.
                        </li>
                        <li>Let <var data-type=3D"double">decode timestamp<=
/var> equal 0.
                        </li>
                      </ol>
                    </dd>
                    <dt>
                      Otherwise:
                    </dt>
                    <dd>
                      <ol>
                        <li>Let <var data-type=3D"double">presentation time=
stamp</var> be a double precision floating point
                        representation of the coded frame's <a data-link-ty=
pe=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#presenta=
tion-timestamp" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-presentation-timestamp-=
18">presentation timestamp</a> in seconds.
                          <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-con=
tainer-generatedID-61"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=
=3D"h-note-61" aria-level=3D"5"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
                            Special processing may be needed to determine t=
he presentation and
                            decode timestamps for timed text frames since t=
his information may not
                            be explicitly present in the underlying format =
or may be dependent on
                            the order of the frames. Some metadata text tra=
cks, like MPEG2-TS PSI
                            data, may only have implied timestamps. Format =
specific rules for these
                            situations <em class=3D"rfc2119">SHOULD</em> be=
 in the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io=
/media-source/#byte-stream-format-specs" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-fo=
r-byte-stream-format-specs-6">byte stream format specifications</a> or in
                            separate extension specifications.
                          </p></div>
                        </li>
                        <li>Let <var data-type=3D"double">decode timestamp<=
/var> be a double precision floating point
                        representation of the coded frame's decode timestam=
p in seconds.
                          <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-con=
tainer-generatedID-62"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=
=3D"h-note-62" aria-level=3D"5"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
                            Implementations don't have to internally store =
timestamps in a double
                            precision floating point representation. This r=
epresentation is used
                            here because it is the representation for times=
tamps in the HTML spec.
                            The intention here is to make the behavior clea=
r without adding
                            unnecessary complexity to the algorithm to deal=
 with the fact that
                            adding a timestampOffset may cause a timestamp =
rollover in the
                            underlying timestamp representation used by the=
 byte stream format.
                            Implementations can use any internal timestamp =
representation they
                            wish, but the addition of timestampOffset <em c=
lass=3D"rfc2119">SHOULD</em> behave in a similar
                            manner to what would happen if a double precisi=
on floating point
                            representation was used.
                          </p></div>
                        </li>
                      </ol>
                    </dd>
                  </dl>
                </li>
                <li>Let <var data-type=3D"double">frame duration</var> be a=
 double precision floating point representation
                of the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" data-lt=3D"cod=
ed frame duration" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-coded-fr=
ame-duration" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-coded-frame-duration-=
6">coded frame's duration</a> in seconds.
                </li>
                <li>If <a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=3D"https://w3c.github=
.io/media-source/#dom-sourcebuffer-mode" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-fo=
r-dom-sourcebuffer-mode-11"><code>mode</code></a> equals "<a data-link-type=
=3D"idl" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-appendmode-sequenc=
e" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-appendmode-sequence-10"><code>se=
quence</code></a>" and
                <a data-link-type=3D"attribute" data-lt=3D"[[group start ti=
mestamp]]" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-group-start-time=
stamp" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-group-start-timestamp-4"><co=
de>[[group start timestamp]]</code></a> is set, then run the following step=
s:
                  <ol>
                    <li>Set <a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=3D"https://w3c.g=
ithub.io/media-source/#dom-sourcebuffer-timestampoffset" class=3D"internalD=
FN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-sourcebuffer-timestampoffset-6"><code>timestampOffset=
</code></a> equal to <a data-link-type=3D"attribute" data-lt=3D"[[group sta=
rt timestamp]]" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-group-start=
-timestamp" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-group-start-timestamp-5=
"><code>[[group start timestamp]]</code></a> minus <var data-type=3D"double=
">presentation timestamp</var>.
                    </li>
                    <li>Set <a data-link-type=3D"attribute" data-lt=3D"[[gr=
oup end timestamp]]" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-group-=
end-timestamp" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-group-end-timestamp-=
4"><code>[[group end timestamp]]</code></a> equal to
                    <a data-link-type=3D"attribute" data-lt=3D"[[group star=
t timestamp]]" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-group-start-=
timestamp" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-group-start-timestamp-6"=
><code>[[group start timestamp]]</code></a>.
                    </li>
                    <li>Set the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=
=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#need-RAP-flag" class=3D"internalDFN=
" id=3D"ref-for-need-RAP-flag-3">need random access point flag</a> on all <=
a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-so=
urce/#track-buffer" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-track-buffer-28">tr=
ack buffers</a> to true.
                    </li>
                    <li>Unset <a data-link-type=3D"attribute" data-lt=3D"[[=
group start timestamp]]" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-gr=
oup-start-timestamp" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-group-start-ti=
mestamp-7"><code>[[group start timestamp]]</code></a>.
                    </li>
                  </ol>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <p>
                    If <a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=3D"https://w3c.github=
.io/media-source/#dom-sourcebuffer-timestampoffset" class=3D"internalDFN" i=
d=3D"ref-for-dom-sourcebuffer-timestampoffset-7"><code>timestampOffset</cod=
e></a> is not 0, then run the following steps:
                  </p>
                  <ol>
                    <li>Add <a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=3D"https://w3c.g=
ithub.io/media-source/#dom-sourcebuffer-timestampoffset" class=3D"internalD=
FN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-sourcebuffer-timestampoffset-8"><code>timestampOffset=
</code></a> to the <var data-type=3D"double">presentation timestamp</var>.
                    </li>
                    <li>Add <a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=3D"https://w3c.g=
ithub.io/media-source/#dom-sourcebuffer-timestampoffset" class=3D"internalD=
FN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-sourcebuffer-timestampoffset-9"><code>timestampOffset=
</code></a> to the <var data-type=3D"double">decode timestamp</var>.
                    </li>
                  </ol>
                </li>
                <li>Let <var>track buffer</var> equal the <a data-link-type=
=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#track-buff=
er" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-track-buffer-29">track buffer</a> t=
hat the coded frame will be
                added to.
                </li>
                <li>
                  <dl class=3D"switch">
                    <dt>
                      If <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"http=
s://w3c.github.io/media-source/#last-decode-timestamp" class=3D"internalDFN=
" id=3D"ref-for-last-decode-timestamp-2">last decode timestamp</a> for <var=
>track buffer</var> is set and <var data-type=3D"double">decode timestamp</=
var>
                      is less than <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" hr=
ef=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#last-decode-timestamp" class=3D"i=
nternalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-last-decode-timestamp-3">last decode timestamp</a=
>:
                    </dt>
                    <dd>
                      OR
                    </dd>
                    <dt>
                      If <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"http=
s://w3c.github.io/media-source/#last-decode-timestamp" class=3D"internalDFN=
" id=3D"ref-for-last-decode-timestamp-4">last decode timestamp</a> for <var=
>track buffer</var> is set and the difference
                      between <var data-type=3D"double">decode timestamp</v=
ar> and <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io=
/media-source/#last-decode-timestamp" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-l=
ast-decode-timestamp-5">last decode timestamp</a> is greater than 2
                      times <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"h=
ttps://w3c.github.io/media-source/#last-frame-duration" class=3D"internalDF=
N" id=3D"ref-for-last-frame-duration-2">last frame duration</a>:
                    </dt>
                    <dd>
                      <ol>
                        <li>
                          <dl class=3D"switch">
                            <dt>
                              If <a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=3D"https://=
w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-sourcebuffer-mode" class=3D"internalDFN" id=
=3D"ref-for-dom-sourcebuffer-mode-12"><code>mode</code></a> equals "<a data=
-link-type=3D"idl" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-appendmo=
de-segments" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-appendmode-segments-4"=
><code>segments</code></a>":
                            </dt>
                            <dd>
