          </h4><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-s=
ource/#sourcebuffer-coded-frame-removal" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Sectio=
n 5.5.9"></a></div>
         =20
          <p>
            Follow these steps when <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" h=
ref=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-coded-frame" class=3D"intern=
alDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-coded-frame-48">coded frames</a> for a specific ti=
me range need to be removed
            from the SourceBuffer:
          </p>
          <ol>
            <li>Let <var data-type=3D"double">start</var> be the starting <=
a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-so=
urce/#presentation-timestamp" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-presentat=
ion-timestamp-23">presentation timestamp</a> for the removal
            range.
            </li>
            <li>Let <var data-type=3D"unrestricted double">end</var> be the=
 end <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/me=
dia-source/#presentation-timestamp" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-pre=
sentation-timestamp-24">presentation timestamp</a> for the removal
            range.
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                For each <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"http=
s://w3c.github.io/media-source/#track-buffer" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"r=
ef-for-track-buffer-34">track buffer</a> in this <a data-link-type=3D"idl" =
data-lt=3D"SourceBuffer" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-so=
urcebuffer" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-sourcebuffer-104"><code=
>SourceBuffer</code></a>, run the following steps:
              </p>
              <ol>
                <li>Let <var data-type=3D"unrestricted double">remove end t=
imestamp</var> be the current value of
                <a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/med=
ia-source/#dom-mediasource-duration" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-do=
m-mediasource-duration-11"><code>duration</code></a>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <p>
                    If this <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"h=
ttps://w3c.github.io/media-source/#track-buffer" class=3D"internalDFN" id=
=3D"ref-for-track-buffer-35">track buffer</a> has a <a data-link-type=3D"df=
n|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#random-access-po=
int" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-random-access-point-8">random acce=
ss point</a> timestamp that is
                    greater than or equal to <var data-type=3D"unrestricted=
 double">end</var>, then update <var data-type=3D"unrestricted double">remo=
ve end timestamp</var> to that
                    random access point timestamp.
                  </p>
                  <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-g=
eneratedID-71"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-no=
te-71" aria-level=3D"5"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
                    Random access point timestamps can be different across =
tracks because the
                    dependencies between <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-=
op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-coded-frame" class=3D"i=
nternalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-coded-frame-49">coded frames</a> within a tra=
ck are usually different than
                    the dependencies in another track.
                  </p></div>
                </li>
                <li>Remove all media data, from this <a data-link-type=3D"d=
fn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#track-buffer" c=
lass=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-track-buffer-36">track buffer</a>, that =
contain starting
                timestamps greater than or equal to <var data-type=3D"doubl=
e">start</var> and less than the <var>remove end
                timestamp</var>.
                  <ol>
                    <li>
                      <p>
                        For each removed frame, if the frame has a <a data-=
link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#d=
fn-decode-timestamp" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-decode-timesta=
mp-3">decode timestamp</a> equal to
                        the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"h=
ttps://w3c.github.io/media-source/#last-decode-timestamp" class=3D"internal=
DFN" id=3D"ref-for-last-decode-timestamp-9">last decode timestamp</a> for t=
he frame's track, run the following
                        steps:
                      </p>
                      <dl class=3D"switch">
                        <dt>
                          If <a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=3D"https://w3c.=
github.io/media-source/#dom-sourcebuffer-mode" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"=
ref-for-dom-sourcebuffer-mode-14"><code>mode</code></a> equals "<a data-lin=
k-type=3D"idl" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-appendmode-s=
egments" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-appendmode-segments-5"><co=
de>segments</code></a>":
                        </dt>
                        <dd>
                          Set <a data-link-type=3D"attribute" data-lt=3D"[[=
group end timestamp]]" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-grou=
p-end-timestamp" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-group-end-timestam=
p-10"><code>[[group end timestamp]]</code></a> to <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|=
abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#presentation-times=
tamp" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-presentation-timestamp-25">presen=
tation timestamp</a>.
                        </dd>
                        <dt>
                          If <a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=3D"https://w3c.=
github.io/media-source/#dom-sourcebuffer-mode" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"=
ref-for-dom-sourcebuffer-mode-15"><code>mode</code></a> equals "<a data-lin=
k-type=3D"idl" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-appendmode-s=
equence" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-appendmode-sequence-12"><c=
ode>sequence</code></a>":
                        </dt>
                        <dd>
                          Set <a data-link-type=3D"attribute" data-lt=3D"[[=
group start timestamp]]" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-gr=
oup-start-timestamp" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-group-start-ti=
mestamp-9"><code>[[group start timestamp]]</code></a> equal to the
                          <a data-link-type=3D"attribute" data-lt=3D"[[grou=
p end timestamp]]" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-group-en=
d-timestamp" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-group-end-timestamp-11=
"><code>[[group end timestamp]]</code></a>.
                        </dd>
                      </dl>
                    </li>
                    <li>Unset the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" hre=
f=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#last-decode-timestamp" class=3D"in=
ternalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-last-decode-timestamp-10">last decode timestamp</a=
> on all <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.i=
o/media-source/#track-buffer" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-track-buf=
fer-37">track buffers</a>.
                    </li>
                    <li>Unset the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" hre=
f=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#last-frame-duration" class=3D"inte=
rnalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-last-frame-duration-5">last frame duration</a> on al=
l <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media=
-source/#track-buffer" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-track-buffer-38"=
>track buffers</a>.
                    </li>
                    <li>Unset the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" hre=
f=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#highest-end-timestamp" class=3D"in=
ternalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-highest-end-timestamp-9">highest end timestamp</a>=
 on all <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io=
/media-source/#track-buffer" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-track-buff=
er-39">track buffers</a>.
                    </li>
                    <li>Set the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=
=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#need-RAP-flag" class=3D"internalDFN=
" id=3D"ref-for-need-RAP-flag-9">need random access point flag</a> on all <=
a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-so=
urce/#track-buffer" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-track-buffer-40">tr=
ack buffers</a> to true.
                    </li>
                  </ol>
                </li>
                <li>Remove all possible decoding dependencies on the <a dat=
a-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/=
#dfn-coded-frame" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-coded-frame-50">c=
oded frames</a> removed in
                the previous step by removing all <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|=
abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-coded-frame" c=
lass=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-coded-frame-51">coded frames</a> fro=
m this <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/=
media-source/#track-buffer" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-track-buffe=
r-41">track buffer</a>
                between those frames removed in the previous step and the n=
ext <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/med=
ia-source/#random-access-point" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-random-=
access-point-9">random access point</a> after those removed frames.
                  <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-g=
eneratedID-72"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-no=
te-72" aria-level=3D"5"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
                    Removing all <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=
=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-coded-frame" class=3D"internalD=
FN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-coded-frame-52">coded frames</a> until the next <a da=
ta-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source=
/#random-access-point" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-random-access-po=
int-10">random access point</a> is a
                    conservative estimate of the decoding dependencies sinc=
e it assumes all frames
                    between the removed frames and the next random access p=
oint depended on the
                    frames that were removed.
                  </p></div>
                </li>
                <li>
                  <p>
                    If this object is in <a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=3D"=
https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource-activesourcebuffers" cl=
ass=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource-activesourcebuffers-30"><=
code>activeSourceBuffers</code></a>, the <a href=3D"https://html.spec.whatw=
g.org/multipage/media.html#current-playback-position">current playback posi=
tion</a> is greater than or equal to <var data-type=3D"double">start</var> =
and less
                    than the <var data-type=3D"unrestricted double">remove =
end timestamp</var>, and <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"HTMLMed=
iaElement" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#htmlme=
diaelement"><code>HTMLMediaElement</code></a>'s
                    <a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io=
/media-source/#dom-readystate" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-read=
ystate-35"><code>readyState</code></a> is greater than
                    <a data-link-type=3D"const" href=3D"https://html.spec.w=
hatwg.org/multipage/media.html#dom-media-have_metadata"><code>HAVE_METADATA=
</code></a>, then set the <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"HTMLMe=
diaElement" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#htmlm=
ediaelement"><code>HTMLMediaElement</code></a>'s
                    <a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io=
/media-source/#dom-readystate" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-read=
ystate-36"><code>readyState</code></a> attribute to <a data-link-type=3D"co=
nst" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#dom-media-ha=
ve_metadata"><code>HAVE_METADATA</code></a>
                    and stall playback.
                  </p>
                  <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-g=
eneratedID-73"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-no=
te-73" aria-level=3D"5"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
                    Per <code><a href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multi=
page/media.html#ready-states">HTMLMediaElement ready states</a></code> [<ci=
te><a class=3D"bibref" data-link-type=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://w3c.github=
.io/media-source/#bib-html" title=3D"HTML Standard">HTML</a></cite>] logic,=
 <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"HTMLMediaElement" href=3D"https=
://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#htmlmediaelement"><code>HTMLMe=
diaElement</code></a>'s
                    <a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io=
/media-source/#dom-readystate" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-read=
ystate-37"><code>readyState</code></a> changes may trigger events on the
                    HTMLMediaElement.
                  </p></div>
                  <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-g=
eneratedID-74"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-no=
te-74" aria-level=3D"5"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
                    This transition occurs because media data for the curre=
nt position has been
                    removed. Playback cannot progress until media for the <=
a href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#current-playbac=
k-position">current playback position</a> is appended or the
                    <a href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#active-s=
ource-buffer-changes" data-matched-text=3D"[[[#active-source-buffer-changes=
]]]" class=3D"sec-ref"><bdi class=3D"secno">3.15.5 </bdi>
            <span>Changes to selected/enabled track state</span></a>.
                  </p></div>
                </li>
              </ol>
            </li>
            <li>If the <a data-link-type=3D"attribute" data-lt=3D"[[buffer =
full flag]]" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-buffer-full-fl=
ag" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-buffer-full-flag-3"><code>[[buf=
fer full flag]]</code></a> equals true and this object is ready
            to accept more bytes, then set the <a data-link-type=3D"attribu=
te" data-lt=3D"[[buffer full flag]]" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-so=
urce/#dfn-buffer-full-flag" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-buffer-=
full-flag-4"><code>[[buffer full flag]]</code></a> to false.
            </li>
          </ol>
        </section>
        <section id=3D"sourcebuffer-coded-frame-eviction"><div class=3D"hea=
der-wrapper"><h4 id=3D"x5-5-10-coded-frame-eviction"><bdi class=3D"secno">5=
.5.10 </bdi>
            <dfn id=3D"dfn-coded-frame-eviction" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspop=
up=3D"dialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">Coded Frame Eviction</dfn>
          </h4><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-s=
ource/#sourcebuffer-coded-frame-eviction" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Secti=
on 5.5.10"></a></div>
         =20
          <p>
            This algorithm is run to free up space in this <a data-link-typ=
e=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"SourceBuffer" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-sour=
ce/#dom-sourcebuffer" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-sourcebuffer-=
105"><code>SourceBuffer</code></a> when new data is
            appended.
          </p>
          <ol>
            <li>Let <var data-type=3D"BufferSource">new data</var> equal th=
e data that is about to be appended to this
            SourceBuffer.
              <div class=3D"issue" id=3D"issue-container-number-289"><div r=
ole=3D"heading" class=3D"issue-title marker" id=3D"h-issue-1" aria-level=3D=
"5"><a href=3D"https://github.com/w3c/media-source/issues/289"><span class=
=3D"issue-number">Issue 289</span></a><span class=3D"issue-label">: Editori=
al? Coded Frame eviction algorithm needs to note that "buffer full flag" ma=
y be updated immediately based on |new data|</span></div><div class=3D"">
                <p>
                  Need to recognize step here that implementations <em clas=
s=3D"rfc2119">MAY</em> decide to set
                  <a data-link-type=3D"attribute" data-lt=3D"[[buffer full =
flag]]" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-buffer-full-flag" c=
lass=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-buffer-full-flag-5"><code>[[buffer f=
ull flag]]</code></a> true here if it predicts that processing
                  <var data-type=3D"BufferSource">new data</var> in additio=
n to any existing bytes in <a data-link-type=3D"attribute" data-lt=3D"[[inp=
ut buffer]]" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-input-buffer" =
class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-input-buffer-14"><code>[[input buff=
er]]</code></a>
                  would exceed the capacity of the <a data-link-type=3D"idl=
" data-lt=3D"SourceBuffer" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-=
sourcebuffer" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-sourcebuffer-106"><co=
de>SourceBuffer</code></a>. Such a step enables more
                  proactive push-back from implementations before accepting=
 <var data-type=3D"BufferSource">new data</var> which would
                  overflow resources, for example. In practice, at least on=
e implementation already
                  does this.
                </p>
              </div></div>
            </li>
            <li>If the <a data-link-type=3D"attribute" data-lt=3D"[[buffer =
full flag]]" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-buffer-full-fl=
ag" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-buffer-full-flag-6"><code>[[buf=
fer full flag]]</code></a> equals false, then abort these steps.
            </li>
            <li>Let <var data-type=3D"normalized TimeRanges">removal ranges=
</var> equal a list of presentation time ranges
            that can be evicted from the presentation to make room for the =
<var data-type=3D"BufferSource">new data</var>.
              <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-gener=
atedID-75"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-7=
5" aria-level=3D"5"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
                Implementations <em class=3D"rfc2119">MAY</em> use differen=
t methods for selecting <var data-type=3D"normalized TimeRanges">removal ra=
nges</var> so web
                applications <em class=3D"rfc2119">SHOULD NOT</em> depend o=
n a specific behavior. The web application can use
                the <a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io=
/media-source/#dom-sourcebuffer-buffered" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-f=
or-dom-sourcebuffer-buffered-4"><code>buffered</code></a> attribute to obse=
rve whether portions of the buffered
                data have been evicted.
              </p></div>
            </li>
            <li>For each range in <var data-type=3D"normalized TimeRanges">=
removal ranges</var>, run the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D=
"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-coded-frame-removal" class=3D"inte=
rnalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-coded-frame-removal-4">coded frame removal</a> a=
lgorithm with
            <var data-type=3D"double">start</var> and <var data-type=3D"unr=
estricted double">end</var> equal to the removal range start and end
            timestamp respectively.
            </li>
          </ol>
        </section>
        <section id=3D"sourcebuffer-audio-splice-frame-algorithm"><div clas=
s=3D"header-wrapper"><h4 id=3D"x5-5-11-audio-splice-frame"><bdi class=3D"se=
cno">5.5.11 </bdi>
            <dfn id=3D"dfn-audio-splice-frame" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=
=3D"dialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">Audio Splice Frame</dfn>
          </h4><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-s=
ource/#sourcebuffer-audio-splice-frame-algorithm" aria-label=3D"Permalink f=
or Section 5.5.11"></a></div>
         =20
          <p>
            Follow these steps when the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-o=
p" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-coded-frame-processing" =
class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-coded-frame-processing-11">coded fr=
ame processing</a> algorithm needs to generate a
            splice frame for two overlapping audio <a data-link-type=3D"dfn=
|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-coded-frame" =
class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-coded-frame-53">coded frames</a>:
          </p>
          <ol>
            <li>Let <var>track buffer</var> be the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn=
|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#track-buffer" cla=
ss=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-track-buffer-42">track buffer</a> that wil=
l contain the splice.
            </li>
            <li>Let <var>new coded frame</var> be the new <a data-link-type=
=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-coded-=
frame" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-coded-frame-54">coded frame<=
/a>, that is being added to <var>track
            buffer</var>, which triggered the need for a splice.
            </li>
            <li>Let <var data-type=3D"double">presentation timestamp</var> =
be the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/=
media-source/#presentation-timestamp" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-p=
resentation-timestamp-26">presentation timestamp</a> for <var>new
            coded frame</var>.
            </li>
            <li>Let <var data-type=3D"double">decode timestamp</var> be the=
 decode timestamp for <var>new coded frame</var>.
            </li>
            <li>Let <var data-type=3D"double">frame duration</var> be the <=
a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-so=
urce/#dfn-coded-frame-duration" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-cod=
ed-frame-duration-7">coded frame duration</a> of <var>new coded frame</var>=
.
            </li>
            <li>Let <var>overlapped frame</var> be the <a data-link-type=3D=
"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-coded-fra=
me" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-coded-frame-55">coded frame</a>=
 in <var>track buffer</var> with a
            <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.githu=
b.io/media-source/#presentation-interval" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-f=
or-presentation-interval-2">presentation interval</a> that contains <var da=
ta-type=3D"double">presentation timestamp</var>.
            </li>
            <li>Update <var data-type=3D"double">presentation timestamp</va=
r> and <var data-type=3D"double">decode timestamp</var> to the nearest audi=
o sample
            timestamp based on sample rate of the audio in <var>overlapped =
frame</var>. If a timestamp is
            equidistant from both audio sample timestamps, then use the hig=
her timestamp (e.g.,
            <code>floor(x * sample_rate + 0.5) / sample_rate</code>).
              <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-gener=
atedID-76"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-7=
6" aria-level=3D"5"><span>Note</span></div><div class=3D"">
                <p>
                  For example, given the following values:
                </p>
                <ul>
                  <li>The <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"htt=
ps://w3c.github.io/media-source/#presentation-timestamp" class=3D"internalD=
FN" id=3D"ref-for-presentation-timestamp-27">presentation timestamp</a> of =
<var>overlapped frame</var> equals 10.
                  </li>
                  <li>The sample rate of <var>overlapped frame</var> equals=
 8000 Hz
                  </li>
                  <li><var data-type=3D"double">presentation timestamp</var=
> equals 10.01255
                  </li>
                  <li><var data-type=3D"double">decode timestamp</var> equa=
ls 10.01255
                  </li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                  <var data-type=3D"double">presentation timestamp</var> an=
d <var data-type=3D"double">decode timestamp</var> are updated to 10.0125 s=
ince
                  10.01255 is closer to 10 + 100/8000 (10.0125) than 10 + 1=
01/8000 (10.012625)
                </p>
              </div></div>
            </li>
            <li>If the user agent does not support crossfading then run the=
 following steps:
              <ol>
                <li>Remove <var>overlapped frame</var> from <var>track buff=
er</var>.
                </li>
                <li>Add a silence frame to <var>track buffer</var> with the=
 following properties:
                  <ul>
                    <li>The <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"h=
ttps://w3c.github.io/media-source/#presentation-timestamp" class=3D"interna=
lDFN" id=3D"ref-for-presentation-timestamp-28">presentation timestamp</a> s=
et to the <var>overlapped frame</var> <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op"=
 href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#presentation-timestamp" class=
=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-presentation-timestamp-29">presentation time=
stamp</a>.
                    </li>
                    <li>The <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"h=
ttps://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-decode-timestamp" class=3D"internalD=
FN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-decode-timestamp-4">decode timestamp</a> set to the <=
var>overlapped frame</var> <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"ht=
tps://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-decode-timestamp" class=3D"internalDF=
N" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-decode-timestamp-5">decode timestamp</a>.
                    </li>
                    <li>The <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"h=
ttps://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-coded-frame-duration" class=3D"inter=
nalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-coded-frame-duration-8">coded frame duration</a> =
set to difference between <var>presentation
                    timestamp</var> and the <var>overlapped frame</var> <a =
data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-sour=
ce/#presentation-timestamp" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-presentatio=
n-timestamp-30">presentation timestamp</a>.
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                  <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-g=
eneratedID-77"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-no=
te-77" aria-level=3D"5"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
                    Some implementations <em class=3D"rfc2119">MAY</em> app=
ly fades to/from silence to coded frames on either
                    side of the inserted silence to make the transition les=
s jarring.
                  </p></div>
                </li>
                <li>Return to caller without providing a splice frame.
                  <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-g=
eneratedID-78"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-no=
te-78" aria-level=3D"5"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
                    This is intended to allow <var>new coded frame</var> to=
 be added to the <var>track buffer</var>
                    as if <var>overlapped frame</var> had not been in the <=
var>track buffer</var> to begin with.
                  </p></div>
                </li>
              </ol>
            </li>
            <li>Let <var data-type=3D"double">frame end timestamp</var> equ=
al the sum of <var data-type=3D"double">presentation timestamp</var> and
            <var data-type=3D"double">frame duration</var>.
            </li>
            <li>Let <var data-type=3D"double">splice end timestamp</var> eq=
ual the sum of <var data-type=3D"double">presentation timestamp</var> and t=
he
            splice duration of 5 milliseconds.
            </li>
            <li>Let <var>fade out coded frames</var> equal <var>overlapped =
frame</var> as well as any additional
            frames in <var>track buffer</var> that have a <a data-link-type=
=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#presentati=
on-timestamp" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-presentation-timestamp-31=
">presentation timestamp</a> greater than
            <var data-type=3D"double">presentation timestamp</var> and less=
 than <var data-type=3D"double">splice end timestamp</var>.
            </li>
            <li>Remove all the frames included in <var>fade out coded frame=
s</var> from <var>track buffer</var>.
            </li>
            <li>Return a splice frame with the following properties:
              <ul>
                <li>The <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https=
://w3c.github.io/media-source/#presentation-timestamp" class=3D"internalDFN=
" id=3D"ref-for-presentation-timestamp-32">presentation timestamp</a> set t=
o the <var>overlapped frame</var> <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" hre=
f=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#presentation-timestamp" class=3D"i=
nternalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-presentation-timestamp-33">presentation timestamp=
</a>.
                </li>
                <li>The <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https=
://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-decode-timestamp" class=3D"internalDFN" =
id=3D"ref-for-dfn-decode-timestamp-6">decode timestamp</a> set to the <var>=
overlapped frame</var> <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https:=
//w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-decode-timestamp" class=3D"internalDFN" i=
d=3D"ref-for-dfn-decode-timestamp-7">decode timestamp</a>.
                </li>
                <li>The <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https=
://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-coded-frame-duration" class=3D"internalD=
FN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-coded-frame-duration-9">coded frame duration</a> set =
to difference between <var data-type=3D"double">frame end timestamp</var>
                and the <var>overlapped frame</var> <a data-link-type=3D"df=
n|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#presentation-tim=
estamp" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-presentation-timestamp-34">pres=
entation timestamp</a>.
                </li>
                <li>The fade out coded frames equals <var>fade out coded fr=
ames</var>.
                </li>
                <li>The fade in coded frame equals <var>new coded frame</va=
r>.
                  <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-g=
eneratedID-79"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-no=
te-79" aria-level=3D"5"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
                    If the <var>new coded frame</var> is less than 5 millis=
econds in duration, then coded
                    frames that are appended after the <var>new coded frame=
</var> will be needed to properly
                    render the splice.
                  </p></div>
                </li>
                <li>The splice timestamp equals <var data-type=3D"double">p=
resentation timestamp</var>.
                </li>
              </ul>
              <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-gener=
atedID-80"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-8=
0" aria-level=3D"5"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
                See the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https=
://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-audio-splice-rendering" class=3D"interna=
lDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-audio-splice-rendering-1">audio splice rendering</a=
> algorithm for details on how this splice frame
                is rendered.
              </p></div>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </section>
        <section id=3D"sourcebuffer-audio-splice-rendering-algorithm"><div =
class=3D"header-wrapper"><h4 id=3D"x5-5-12-audio-splice-rendering"><bdi cla=
ss=3D"secno">5.5.12 </bdi>
            <dfn id=3D"dfn-audio-splice-rendering" tabindex=3D"0" aria-hasp=
opup=3D"dialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">Audio Splice Rendering</dfn>
          </h4><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-s=
ource/#sourcebuffer-audio-splice-rendering-algorithm" aria-label=3D"Permali=
nk for Section 5.5.12"></a></div>
         =20
          <p>
            The following steps are run when a spliced frame, generated by =
the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/med=
ia-source/#dfn-audio-splice-frame" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-=
audio-splice-frame-2">audio splice frame</a> algorithm, needs to be rendere=
d by the media element:
          </p>
          <ol>
            <li>Let <var>fade out coded frames</var> be the <a data-link-ty=
pe=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-code=
d-frame" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-coded-frame-56">coded fram=
es</a> that are faded out during the
            splice.
            </li>
            <li>Let <var>fade in coded frames</var> be the <a data-link-typ=
e=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-coded=
-frame" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-coded-frame-57">coded frame=
s</a> that are faded in during the
            splice.
            </li>
            <li>Let <var data-type=3D"double">presentation timestamp</var> =
be the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/=
media-source/#presentation-timestamp" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-p=
resentation-timestamp-35">presentation timestamp</a> of the first
            coded frame in <var>fade out coded frames</var>.
            </li>
            <li>Let <var data-type=3D"double">end timestamp</var> be the su=
m of the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.i=
o/media-source/#presentation-timestamp" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for=
-presentation-timestamp-36">presentation timestamp</a> and the
            <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.githu=
b.io/media-source/#dfn-coded-frame-duration" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"re=
f-for-dfn-coded-frame-duration-10">coded frame duration</a> of the last fra=
me in <var>fade in coded frames</var>.
            </li>
            <li>Let <var data-type=3D"double">splice timestamp</var> be the=
 <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-=
source/#presentation-timestamp" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-present=
ation-timestamp-37">presentation timestamp</a> where the splice
            starts. This corresponds with the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abst=
ract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#presentation-timestamp=
" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-presentation-timestamp-38">presentati=
on timestamp</a> of the first frame in
            <var>fade in coded frames</var>.
            </li>
            <li>Let <var data-type=3D"double">splice end timestamp</var> eq=
ual <var data-type=3D"double">splice timestamp</var> plus five milliseconds=
.
            </li>
            <li>Let <var>fade out samples</var> be the samples generated by=
 decoding <var>fade out coded
            frames</var>.
            </li>
            <li>Trim <var>fade out samples</var> so that it only contains s=
amples between <var>presentation
            timestamp</var> and <var data-type=3D"double">splice end timest=
amp</var>.
            </li>
            <li>Let <var>fade in samples</var> be the samples generated by =
decoding <var>fade in coded frames</var>.
            </li>
            <li>If <var>fade out samples</var> and <var>fade in samples</va=
r> do not have a common sample rate and
            channel layout, then convert <var>fade out samples</var> and <v=
ar>fade in samples</var> to a common
            sample rate and channel layout.
            </li>
            <li>Let <var>output samples</var> be a buffer to hold the outpu=
t samples.
            </li>
            <li>Apply a linear gain fade out with a starting gain of 1 and =
an ending gain of 0 to
            the samples between <var data-type=3D"double">splice timestamp<=
/var> and <var data-type=3D"double">splice end timestamp</var> in <var>fade=
 out
            samples</var>.
            </li>
            <li>Apply a linear gain fade in with a starting gain of 0 and a=
n ending gain of 1 to
            the samples between <var data-type=3D"double">splice timestamp<=
/var> and <var data-type=3D"double">splice end timestamp</var> in <var>fade=
 in samples</var>.
            </li>
            <li>Copy samples between <var data-type=3D"double">presentation=
 timestamp</var> to <var data-type=3D"double">splice timestamp</var> from <=
var>fade out
            samples</var> into <var>output samples</var>.
            </li>
            <li>For each sample between <var data-type=3D"double">splice ti=
mestamp</var> and <var data-type=3D"double">splice end timestamp</var>, com=
pute the
            sum of a sample from <var>fade out samples</var> and the corres=
ponding sample in <var>fade in
            samples</var> and store the result in <var>output samples</var>=
.
            </li>
            <li>Copy samples between <var data-type=3D"double">splice end t=
imestamp</var> to <var data-type=3D"double">end timestamp</var> from <var>f=
ade in
            samples</var> into <var>output samples</var>.
            </li>
            <li>Render <var>output samples</var>.
            </li>
          </ol>
          <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-generated=
ID-81"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-81" a=
ria-level=3D"5"><span>Note</span></div><div class=3D"">
            <p>
              Here is a graphical representation of this algorithm.
            </p><img src=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/audio_splice=
.png" alt=3D"Audio splice diagram">
          </div></div>
        </section>
        <section id=3D"sourcebuffer-text-splice-frame-algorithm"><div class=
=3D"header-wrapper"><h4 id=3D"x5-5-13-text-splice-frame"><bdi class=3D"secn=
o">5.5.13 </bdi>
            <dfn id=3D"dfn-text-splice-frame" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=
=3D"dialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">Text Splice Frame</dfn>
          </h4><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-s=
ource/#sourcebuffer-text-splice-frame-algorithm" aria-label=3D"Permalink fo=
r Section 5.5.13"></a></div>
         =20
          <p>
            Follow these steps when the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-o=
p" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-coded-frame-processing" =
class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-coded-frame-processing-12">coded fr=
ame processing</a> algorithm needs to generate a
            splice frame for two overlapping timed text <a data-link-type=
=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-coded-=
frame" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-coded-frame-58">coded frames=
</a>:
          </p>
          <ol>
            <li>Let <var>track buffer</var> be the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn=
|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#track-buffer" cla=
ss=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-track-buffer-43">track buffer</a> that wil=
l contain the splice.
            </li>
            <li>Let <var>new coded frame</var> be the new <a data-link-type=
=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-coded-=
frame" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-coded-frame-59">coded frame<=
/a>, that is being added to <var>track
            buffer</var>, which triggered the need for a splice.
            </li>
            <li>Let <var data-type=3D"double">presentation timestamp</var> =
be the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/=
media-source/#presentation-timestamp" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-p=
resentation-timestamp-39">presentation timestamp</a> for <var>new
            coded frame</var>
            </li>
            <li>Let <var data-type=3D"double">decode timestamp</var> be the=
 decode timestamp for <var>new coded frame</var>.
            </li>
            <li>Let <var data-type=3D"double">frame duration</var> be the <=
a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-so=
urce/#dfn-coded-frame-duration" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-cod=
ed-frame-duration-11">coded frame duration</a> of <var>new coded frame</var=
>.
            </li>
            <li>Let <var data-type=3D"double">frame end timestamp</var> equ=
al the sum of <var data-type=3D"double">presentation timestamp</var> and
            <var data-type=3D"double">frame duration</var>.
            </li>
            <li>Let <var>first overlapped frame</var> be the <a data-link-t=
ype=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-cod=
ed-frame" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-coded-frame-60">coded fra=
me</a> in <var>track buffer</var> with a
            <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.githu=
b.io/media-source/#presentation-interval" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-f=
or-presentation-interval-3">presentation interval</a> that contains <var da=
ta-type=3D"double">presentation timestamp</var>.
            </li>
            <li>Let <var data-type=3D"double">overlapped presentation times=
tamp</var> be the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c=
.github.io/media-source/#presentation-timestamp" class=3D"internalDFN" id=
=3D"ref-for-presentation-timestamp-40">presentation timestamp</a> of
            the <var>first overlapped frame</var>.
            </li>
            <li>Let <var>overlapped frames</var> equal <var>first overlappe=
d frame</var> as well as any additional
            frames in <var>track buffer</var> that have a <a data-link-type=
=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#presentati=
on-timestamp" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-presentation-timestamp-41=
">presentation timestamp</a> greater than
            <var data-type=3D"double">presentation timestamp</var> and less=
 than <var data-type=3D"double">frame end timestamp</var>.
            </li>
            <li>Remove all the frames included in <var>overlapped frames</v=
ar> from <var>track buffer</var>.
            </li>
            <li>Update the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"ht=
tps://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-coded-frame-duration" class=3D"intern=
alDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-coded-frame-duration-12">coded frame duration</a> =
of the <var>first overlapped frame</var> to
            <var data-type=3D"double">presentation timestamp</var> minus <v=
ar data-type=3D"double">overlapped presentation timestamp</var>.
            </li>
            <li>Add <var>first overlapped frame</var> to the <var>track buf=
fer</var>.
            </li>
            <li>Return to caller without providing a splice frame.
              <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-gener=
atedID-82"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-8=
2" aria-level=3D"5"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
                This is intended to allow <var>new coded frame</var> to be =
added to the <var>track buffer</var> as if
                it hadn't overlapped any frames in <var>track buffer</var> =
to begin with.
              </p></div>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </section>
      </section>
    </section>
