    <section data-cite=3D"WEBIDL mimesniff" data-dfn-for=3D"ManagedMediaSou=
rce" id=3D"managedmediasource-interface"><div class=3D"header-wrapper"><h2 =
id=3D"x7-managedmediasource-interface"><bdi class=3D"secno">7. </bdi>
        <dfn data-export=3D"" data-dfn-type=3D"interface" id=3D"dom-managed=
mediasource" data-idl=3D"interface" data-title=3D"ManagedMediaSource" data-=
dfn-for=3D"" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog"><code>ManagedMediaSour=
ce</code></dfn> interface
      </h2><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-sourc=
e/#managedmediasource-interface" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 7."></=
a></div>
     =20
      <p>
        A <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"ManagedMediaSource" href=3D"=
https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-managedmediasource" class=3D"intern=
alDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-managedmediasource-4"><code>ManagedMediaSource</co=
de></a> is a <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSource" href=3D"http=
s://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource" class=3D"internalDFN" id=
=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource-99"><code>MediaSource</code></a> that actively =
manages its memory content.
        Unlike a <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSource" href=3D"=
https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource" class=3D"internalDFN" =
id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource-100"><code>MediaSource</code></a>, the <a dat=
a-link-type=3D"dfn" href=3D"https://infra.spec.whatwg.org/#user-agent">user=
 agent</a> can evict content through the
        <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io=
/media-source/#dfn-memory-cleanup" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-=
memory-cleanup-1">memory cleanup</a> algorithm from its <a data-link-type=
=3D"idl" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource-source=
buffers" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource-sourcebuffers-=
32"><code>sourceBuffers</code></a>
        (populated with <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"ManagedSourceB=
uffer" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-managedsourcebuffer"=
 class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-managedsourcebuffer-3"><code>Manag=
edSourceBuffer</code></a>) for any reason.
      </p>
      <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-generatedID-8=
3"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-83" aria-=
level=3D"3"><span>Note</span><span class=3D"issue-label">: Eviction reasons=
</span></div><aside class=3D"">
        <p>
          Reasons that the user agent might evict content are implementatio=
n specific and can
          include, but are not limited to, memory and/or hardware limitatio=
ns, change in
          environmental conditions, and so on. Developers shouldn't make as=
sumptions as to why,
          how, or when a user agent might evict content. Instead, developer=
s need to write scripts
          with the assumption that content is constantly and randomly being=
 evicted to avoid
          stalled video playback (i.e., code defensibly and listen for the =
<a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"bufferedchange" href=3D"https://w3c.gi=
thub.io/media-source/#dfn-bufferedchange" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-f=
or-dfn-bufferedchange-1"><code>bufferedchange</code></a>
          event!).
        </p>
      </aside></div>
      <pre class=3D"idl def" id=3D"webidl-1619111096"><span class=3D"idlHea=
der"><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#web=
