      <section id=3D"htmlmediaelement-extensions-seekable"><div class=3D"he=
ader-wrapper"><h3 id=3D"x10-1-htmlmediaelement-s-seekable"><bdi class=3D"se=
cno">10.1 </bdi>
          <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"HTMLMediaElement" href=
=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#htmlmediaelement"><co=
de>HTMLMediaElement</code></a>'s <a data-link-type=3D"attribute" href=3D"ht=
tps://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#dom-media-seekable"><code>s=
eekable</code></a>
        </h3><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-sou=
rce/#htmlmediaelement-extensions-seekable" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Sect=
ion 10.1"></a></div>
       =20
        <p>
          The <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"HTMLMediaElement" =
href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#htmlmediaelement"=
><code>HTMLMediaElement</code></a>'s <a data-link-type=3D"attribute" href=
=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#dom-media-seekable"><=
code>seekable</code></a> attribute returns a new static
          <a href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#norm=
alised-timeranges-object">normalized TimeRanges object</a> created based on=
 the following steps:
        </p>
        <ol>
          <li>If the <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"MediaSource" href=
=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource" class=3D"internalD=
FN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource-104"><code>MediaSource</code></a> was con=
structed in a <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"DedicatedWorkerGlo=
balScope" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/workers.html#dedic=
atedworkerglobalscope"><code>DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope</code></a> that is
          terminated or is closing then return an empty <a data-link-type=
=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"TimeRanges" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/=
multipage/media.html#timeranges"><code>TimeRanges</code></a> object and abo=
rt these
          steps.
            <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-generat=
edID-85"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-85"=
 aria-level=3D"4"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
              This case is intended to handle implementations that may no l=
onger maintain any
              previous information about buffered or seekable media in a Me=
diaSource that was
              constructed in a DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope that has been ter=
minated by
              <a data-link-type=3D"method" data-lt=3D"terminate()" href=3D"=
https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/workers.html#dom-worker-terminate"><=
code>terminate</code></a><code>()</code> or user agent execution of <a data=
-link-type=3D"dfn" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/workers.h=
tml#terminate-a-worker">terminate a worker</a> for the
              MediaSource's DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope, for instance as the=
 eventual result of
              <a data-link-type=3D"method" data-lt=3D"close()" href=3D"http=
s://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/workers.html#dom-dedicatedworkerglobalsc=
ope-close"><code>close</code></a><code>()</code> execution.
            </p></div>
            <div class=3D"issue" id=3D"issue-container-number-277"><div rol=
e=3D"heading" class=3D"issue-title marker" id=3D"h-issue-2" aria-level=3D"4=
"><a href=3D"https://github.com/w3c/media-source/issues/277"><span class=3D=
"issue-number">Issue 277</span></a><span class=3D"issue-label">: MSE-in-Wor=
kers: Consider (eventually) transitioning attached element to error upon te=
rmination of MediaSource's worker/what should media element do? <a class=3D=
"respec-gh-label" href=3D"https://github.com/w3c/media-source/issues/?q=3Di=
s%3Aissue+is%3Aopen+label%3A%22mse-in-workers%22" style=3D"background-color=
: rgb(170, 170, 170); color: rgb(0, 0, 0);" aria-label=3D"GitHub label: mse=
-in-workers">mse-in-workers</a></span></div><div class=3D"">
              <p>
                Should there be some (eventual) media element error transit=
ion in the case of an
                attached worker MediaSource having its context destroyed? T=
he experimental Chromium
                implementation of worker MSE just keeps the element readySt=
ate, networkState and
                error the same as prior to that context destruction, though=
 the seekable and
                buffered attributes each report an empty TimeRange.
              </p>
            </div></div>
          </li>
          <li>Let <var data-type=3D"unrestricted double">recent duration</v=
ar> and <var data-type=3D"normalized
          TimeRanges">recent live seekable range</var> respectively be the =
recent values of <a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/me=
dia-source/#dom-mediasource-duration" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-d=
om-mediasource-duration-12"><code>duration</code></a> and
          <a data-link-type=3D"attribute" data-lt=3D"[[live seekable range]=
]" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-live-seekable-range" cla=
ss=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-live-seekable-range-6"><code>[[live se=
ekable range]]</code></a>, determined as follows:
            <dl class=3D"switch">
