    <section id=3D"byte-stream-formats"><div class=3D"header-wrapper"><h2 i=
d=3D"x14-byte-stream-formats"><bdi class=3D"secno">14. </bdi>
        <dfn data-export=3D"" id=3D"dfn-byte-stream-formats" tabindex=3D"0"=
 aria-haspopup=3D"dialog" data-dfn-type=3D"dfn">Byte Stream Formats</dfn>
      </h2><a class=3D"self-link" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-sourc=
e/#byte-stream-formats" aria-label=3D"Permalink for Section 14."></a></div>
     =20
      <p>
        The bytes provided through <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"app=
endBuffer()" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-sourcebuffer-a=
ppendbuffer" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-sourcebuffer-appendbuf=
fer-12"><code>appendBuffer</code></a><code>()</code> for a <a data-link-typ=
e=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"SourceBuffer" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-sour=
ce/#dom-sourcebuffer" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-sourcebuffer-=
136"><code>SourceBuffer</code></a> form a
        logical byte stream. The format and semantics of these byte streams=
 are defined in <dfn id=3D"byte-stream-format-specs" data-plurals=3D"byte s=
tream format specification" tabindex=3D"0" aria-haspopup=3D"dialog" data-df=
n-type=3D"dfn">byte stream format specifications</dfn>. The byte stream for=
mat
        registry [<cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-link-type=3D"biblio" href=
=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#bib-mse-registry" title=3D"Media So=
urce Extensions=E2=84=A2 Byte Stream Format Registry">MSE-REGISTRY</a></cit=
e>] provides mappings between a MIME type that may be passed to
        <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"addSourceBuffer()" href=3D"htt=
ps://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource-addsourcebuffer" class=3D"=
internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource-addsourcebuffer-12"><code>addSou=
rceBuffer</code></a><code>()</code>, <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"i=
sTypeSupported()" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasour=
ce-istypesupported" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource-ist=
ypesupported-4"><code>isTypeSupported</code></a><code>()</code> or
        <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"changeType()" href=3D"https://=
w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-sourcebuffer-changetype" class=3D"internalD=
FN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-sourcebuffer-changetype-17"><code>changeType</code></=
a><code>()</code> and the byte stream format expected by a <a data-link-typ=
e=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"SourceBuffer" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-sour=
ce/#dom-sourcebuffer" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-sourcebuffer-=
137"><code>SourceBuffer</code></a>
        using that MIME type for parsing newly appended data. Implementatio=
ns are encouraged to
        register mappings for byte stream formats they support to facilitat=
e interoperability. The
        byte stream format registry [<cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-link-ty=
pe=3D"biblio" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#bib-mse-registry"=
 title=3D"Media Source Extensions=E2=84=A2 Byte Stream Format Registry">MSE=
-REGISTRY</a></cite>] is the authoritative source for these
        mappings. If an implementation claims to support a MIME type listed=
 in the registry, its
        <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"SourceBuffer" href=3D"https://=
w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-sourcebuffer" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"r=
ef-for-dom-sourcebuffer-138"><code>SourceBuffer</code></a> implementation <=
em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST</em> conform to the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abst=
ract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#byte-stream-format-spe=
cs" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-byte-stream-format-specs-7">byte st=
ream format specification</a>
        listed in the registry entry.
      </p>
      <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-generatedID-9=
3"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-92" aria-=
level=3D"3"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
        The byte stream format specifications in the registry are not inten=
ded to define new
        storage formats. They simply outline the subset of existing storage=
 format structures that
        implementations of this specification will accept.
      </p></div>
      <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-generatedID-9=
4"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-93" aria-=
level=3D"3"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
        Byte stream format parsing and validation is implemented in the <a =
data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-sour=
ce/#dfn-segment-parser-loop" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-segmen=
t-parser-loop-5">segment parser loop</a>
        algorithm.
      </p></div>
      <p>
        This section provides general requirements for all byte stream form=
at specifications:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>A byte stream format specification <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST</=
em> define <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github=
.io/media-source/#dfn-initialization-segment" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"r=
ef-for-dfn-initialization-segment-33">initialization segments</a> and <a da=
ta-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source=
/#dfn-media-segment" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-media-segment-=
15">media segments</a>.
        </li>
        <li>A byte stream format <em class=3D"rfc2119">SHOULD</em> provide =
references for sourcing <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"AudioTra=
ck" href=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#audiotrack"><=
code>AudioTrack</code></a>,
        <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"VideoTrack" href=3D"http=
s://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#videotrack"><code>VideoTrack<=
/code></a>, and <a data-link-type=3D"interface" data-lt=3D"TextTrack" href=
=3D"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#texttrack"><code>Text=
Track</code></a> attribute values from data in <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abs=
tract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-initialization-se=
gment" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-initialization-segment-34">i=
nitialization segments</a>.
          <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-generated=
ID-95"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-94" a=
ria-level=3D"3"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
            If the byte stream format covers a format similar to one covere=
d in the in-band tracks
            spec [<cite><a class=3D"bibref" data-link-type=3D"biblio" href=
=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#bib-inbandtracks" title=3D"Sourcing=
 In-band Media Resource Tracks from Media Containers into HTML">INBANDTRACK=
S</a></cite>], then it <em class=3D"rfc2119">SHOULD</em> try to use the sam=
e attribute mappings so that
            Media Source Extensions playback and non-Media Source Extension=
s playback provide the
            same track information.
          </p></div>
        </li>
        <li>It <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST</em> be possible to identify segm=
ent boundaries and segment type (initialization or
        media) by examining the byte stream alone.
        </li>
        <li>The user agent <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST</em> run the <a data-=
link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#d=
fn-append-error" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-append-error-8">ap=
pend error</a> algorithm when any of the following
        conditions are met:
          <ol>
            <li>
              <p>
                The number and type of tracks are not consistent.
              </p>
              <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-gener=
atedID-96"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-9=
5" aria-level=3D"3"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
                For example, if the first <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract=
-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-initialization-segment=
" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-initialization-segment-35">initia=
lization segment</a> has 2 audio tracks and 1 video
                track, then all <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=
=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-initialization-segment" class=
=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-initialization-segment-36">initializatio=
n segments</a> that follow it in the byte stream <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST=
</em>
                describe 2 audio tracks and 1 video track.
              </p></div>
            </li>
            <li><a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.g=
ithub.io/media-source/#dfn-track-id" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-df=
n-track-id-9">Track IDs</a> are not the same across <a data-link-type=3D"df=
n|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-initializati=
on-segment" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-initialization-segment-=
37">initialization segments</a>, for segments
            describing multiple tracks of a single type (e.g., 2 audio trac=
ks).
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                Unsupported codec changes occur across <a data-link-type=3D=
"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-initializ=
ation-segment" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-initialization-segme=
nt-38">initialization segments</a>.
              </p>
              <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-gener=
atedID-97"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-9=
6" aria-level=3D"3"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
                See the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https=
://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-initialization-segment-received" class=
=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-initialization-segment-received-2">initi=
alization segment received</a> algorithm,
                <a data-link-type=3D"idl" data-lt=3D"addSourceBuffer()" hre=
f=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-mediasource-addsourcebuffer" c=
lass=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-mediasource-addsourcebuffer-13"><cod=
e>addSourceBuffer</code></a><code>()</code> and <a data-link-type=3D"idl" d=
ata-lt=3D"changeType()" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dom-sou=
rcebuffer-changetype" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-sourcebuffer-=
changetype-18"><code>changeType</code></a><code>()</code> for details and
                examples of codec changes.
              </p></div>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </li>
        <li>The user agent <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST</em> support the foll=
owing:
          <ol>
            <li><a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.g=
ithub.io/media-source/#dfn-track-id" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-df=
n-track-id-10">Track IDs</a> changing across <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstr=
act-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-initialization-segm=
ent" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-initialization-segment-39">ini=
tialization segments</a> if the segments describe
            only one track of each type.
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                Video frame size changes. The user agent <em class=3D"rfc21=
19">MUST</em> support seamless playback.
              </p>
              <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-gener=
atedID-98"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-9=
7" aria-level=3D"3"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
                This will cause the &lt;video&gt; display region to change =
size if the web
                application does not use CSS or HTML attributes (width/heig=
ht) to constrain the
                element size.
              </p></div>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                Audio channel count changes. The user agent <em class=3D"rf=
c2119">MAY</em> support this seamlessly and could
                trigger downmixing.
              </p>
              <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-gener=
atedID-99"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-9=
8" aria-level=3D"3"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
                This is a quality of implementation issue because changing =
the channel count may
                require reinitializing the audio device, resamplers, and ch=
annel mixers which tends
                to be audible.
              </p></div>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </li>
        <li>The following rules apply to all <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstr=
act-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-media-segment" clas=
s=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-media-segment-16">media segments</a> wi=
thin a byte stream. A user agent
        <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST</em>:
          <ol>
            <li>Map all timestamps to the same <a href=3D"https://html.spec=
.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#media-timeline">media timeline</a>.
            </li>
            <li>Support seamless playback of <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstr=
act-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-media-segment" clas=
s=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-media-segment-17">media segments</a> ha=
ving a timestamp gap smaller than
            the audio frame size. User agents <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST NO=
T</em> reflect these gaps in the
            <a data-link-type=3D"idl" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-s=
ource/#dom-sourcebuffer-buffered" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dom-s=
ourcebuffer-buffered-11"><code>buffered</code></a> attribute.
              <div class=3D"note" role=3D"note" id=3D"issue-container-gener=
atedID-100"><div role=3D"heading" class=3D"note-title marker" id=3D"h-note-=
99" aria-level=3D"3"><span>Note</span></div><p class=3D"">
                This is intended to simplify switching between audio stream=
s where the frame
                boundaries don't always line up across encodings (e.g., Vor=
bis).
              </p></div>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </li>
        <li>The user agent <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST</em> run the <a data-=
link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#d=
fn-append-error" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-append-error-9">ap=
pend error</a> algorithm when any combination of an
        <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io=
/media-source/#dfn-initialization-segment" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-=
for-dfn-initialization-segment-40">initialization segment</a> and any conti=
guous sequence of <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c=
.github.io/media-source/#dfn-media-segment" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref=
-for-dfn-media-segment-18">media segments</a> satisfies the
        following conditions:
          <ol>
            <li>The number and type (audio, video, text, etc.) of all track=
s in the <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.i=
o/media-source/#dfn-media-segment" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-=
media-segment-19">media segments</a> are not identified.
            </li>
            <li>The decoding capabilities needed to decode each track (i.e.=
, codec and codec
            parameters) are not provided.
            </li>
            <li>Encryption parameters necessary to decrypt the content (exc=
ept the encryption key
            itself) are not provided for all encrypted tracks.
            </li>
            <li>All information necessary to decode and render the earliest=
 <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-=
source/#random-access-point" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-random-acc=
ess-point-11">random access point</a>
            in the sequence of <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=
=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-media-segment" class=3D"interna=
lDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-media-segment-20">media segments</a> and all subseq=
uence samples in the sequence (in
            presentation time) are not provided. This includes in particula=
r,
              <ul>
                <li>Information that determines the <a href=3D"https://html=
.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/media.html#concept-video-intrinsic-width">intrin=
sic width and height</a> of
                the video (specifically, this requires either the picture o=
r pixel aspect ratio,
                together with the encoded resolution).
                </li>
                <li>Information necessary to convert the video decoder outp=
ut to a format suitable
                for display
                </li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>Information necessary to compute the global <a data-link-ty=
pe=3D"dfn|abstract-op" href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#presenta=
tion-timestamp" class=3D"internalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-presentation-timestamp-=
42">presentation timestamp</a> of every
            sample in the sequence of <a data-link-type=3D"dfn|abstract-op"=
 href=3D"https://w3c.github.io/media-source/#dfn-media-segment" class=3D"in=
ternalDFN" id=3D"ref-for-dfn-media-segment-21">media segments</a> is not pr=
ovided.
            </li>
          </ol>
          <p>
            For example, if I1 is associated with M1, M2, M3 then the above=
 <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST</em> hold for all the
            combinations I1+M1, I1+M2, I1+M1+M2, I1+M2+M3, etc.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Byte stream specifications <em class=3D"rfc2119">MUST</em> at a min=
imum define constraints which ensure that the above
        requirements hold. Additional constraints <em class=3D"rfc2119">MAY=
</em> be defined, for example to simplify
        implementation.
      </p>
    </section>
